Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00

; KORSiOS - [Audio / Multimedia]• Stability • Disable hardware audio offload
; ID: Audio_DisableHardwareOffload
; DESC: Disables hardware audio offloading (offloading audio processing to the hardware).
; IMPACT: • Forces audio processing on the CPU/Windows side rather than via dedicated hardware.
; IMPACT: • May improve audio stability (fewer dropouts, glitches) with certain drivers/sound cards.
; IMPACT: • Makes audio behavior more predictable, especially at low latency.
; RISK: • Slightly higher CPU load for audio processing.
; RISK: • Possible loss of hardware optimizations on perfectly compatible hardware.
; RISK: • Variable impact depending on the sound card and drivers.
; NOTE: Audio stability/compatibility setting: useful if you are experiencing audio issues (crackling, dropouts), otherwise optional.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\MMDevices\Audio]
"DisableAudioOffload"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Audio / Multimedia]• Microphone • Disable Automatic Microphone Enhancement
; ID: Audio_DisableMicrophoneEnhancement
; DESC: Disables audio enhancements for input devices (microphone).
; IMPACT: • Turns off software audio processing (noise reduction, echo, AGC, effects).
; IMPACT: • The microphone signal becomes more raw and faithful, with potentially reduced latency.
; IMPACT: • May improve stability and avoid conflicts with certain drivers or audio software.
; RISK: • Loss of useful automatic corrections (ambient noise, normalization).
; RISK: • Perceived quality may depend more on the microphone and environment.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or security.
; NOTE: Audio setting / pro control: recommended if you are using a good microphone or external processing (DAW, audio interface), otherwise adjust as needed.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\MMDevices\Audio\Capture]
"DisableEnhancements"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Audio / Multimedia]• Stability • Force Real-Time Audio Priority
; ID: Audio_RealTimeAudioPriority
; DESC: Increases the priority of audio tasks for improved real-time stability.																					 
; IMPACT: • Assigns high priority to audio tasks via MMCSS.
; IMPACT: • Prioritizes CPU allocation for audio.
; IMPACT: • Reduces latency, crackling, and dropouts during playback/recording (DAW, VoIP, streaming, gaming).
; RISK: • Fewer resources available for other background tasks during sustained audio load.
; RISK: • Gains vary depending on drivers and hardware; sometimes a neutral effect.
; RISK: • No risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: Real•time audio setting: recommended for audio creation and streaming to ensure smooth playback.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Multimedia\SystemProfile\Tasks\Audio]
"Priority"=dword:00000006
"Scheduling Category"="High"

; KORSiOS - [Audio / Multimedia]• Communications • Disable automatic volume reduction (e.g., Discord/game)
; ID: Audio_DisableVolumeReduction
; DESC: Disables automatic volume reduction for other sounds during communications.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from lowering application volume when audio communication is detected (call, VoIP, voice chat).
; IMPACT: • The overall volume remains constant, without automatic attenuation.
; IMPACT: • Improves comfort for gaming, music, or streaming during communications.
; RISK: • Communication voice less audible if the overall volume is high.
; RISK: • Sometimes requires manual volume adjustment.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or security.
; NOTE: Audio/comfort setting: avoids volume fluctuations imposed by Windows, highly recommended for multimedia.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Multimedia\Audio]
"UserDuckingPreference"=dword:00000003

; KORSiOS - [Audio / Multimedia]• Comfort • Background Audio Playback
; ID: Audio_BackgroundAudioPlayback
; DESC: Allows background audio playback for the user.
; IMPACT: • Allows audio applications (players, browsers, multimedia apps) to continue playing sound even when they are not in the foreground.
; IMPACT: • Prevents audio dropouts when switching windows or changing focus.
; IMPACT: • Improves multitasking comfort (music, podcasts, streams while gaming or working).
; RISK: • Slightly increased CPU usage if multiple audio apps remain active.
; RISK: • Risk of unwanted simultaneous sounds if multiple applications play audio in the background.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or security.
; NOTE: Multimedia comfort setting: essential for modern audio multitasking.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Multimedia\Audio]
"AllowBackgroundAudio"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Audio / Multimedia]• Stability • Disable Audio Engine Power Saving
; ID: Audio_AudioEnginePower
; DESC: Disables Windows audio power•saving mechanisms.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from putting audio components to sleep or reducing their activity.
; IMPACT: • Improves audio stability (fewer dropouts, pops, and wake•up delays).
; IMPACT: • Keeps audio devices in a constant active state, useful for real-time applications (games, DAWs, VoIP).
; RISK: • Slightly increased power consumption, especially on laptops.
; RISK: • Negligible impact on desktop PCs.
; RISK: • No risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: Audio stability/low latency setting: recommended to avoid audio issues related to sleep mode, highly relevant for gaming and professional audio.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Audio]
"DisablePowerSaving"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Audio / Multimedia]• Comfort • Disable all system sounds
; ID: Audio_DisableSystemSound
; DESC: Disables Windows audio power-saving mechanisms.
; IMPACT: • Forces the Windows sound scheme to No sound.
; IMPACT: • Suppresses event sounds (notifications, errors, shutdowns, etc.).
; IMPACT: • Does not affect application sounds (games, Spotify, etc.), only Windows sounds.
; RISK: • You may miss some useful audible feedback (errors, alerts).
; RISK: • No risk to stability or performance.
; NOTE: Silent/clean setting: ideal for a gaming or audio setup where you want no background Windows sounds.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\AppEvents\Schemes]
@=".None"

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• Search • "Search" icon only (magnifying glass)
; ID: Taskbar_SearchIconOnly
; DESC: Displays the search box as an icon in the taskbar.
; IMPACT: • Replaces the entire search bar with a search icon.
; IMPACT: • Keeps this choice cached to prevent visual resets.
; IMPACT: • More compact and streamlined taskbar, while maintaining access to search.
; RISK: • Reduced visibility of the search function (icon instead of a text field).
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Ergonomics/minimalism setting: lightens the taskbar without losing search functionality.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Search]
"SearchboxTaskbarMode"=dword:00000001
"SearchboxTaskbarModeCache"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• Search • Hidden "Search"
; ID: Taskbar_HiddenSearch
; DESC: Hides the search box in the taskbar.
; IMPACT: • Replaces the entire search bar with a search icon.
; IMPACT: • Keeps this choice cached to prevent visual resets.
; IMPACT: • More compact and streamlined taskbar, while maintaining access to search.
; RISK: • Reduced visibility of the search function (icon instead of a text field).
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Ergonomics/minimalism setting: lightens the taskbar without losing search functionality.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Search]
"SearchboxTaskbarMode"=dword:00000000
"SearchboxTaskbarModeCache"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• Built-in apps • Disable “Meet Now” display
; ID: Taskbar_DisableMeetNow
; DESC: Hides the “Meet Now” button (Instant Meeting / Skype) in the notification area.
; IMPACT: • Removes the “Meet Now” icon from the taskbar (system area).
; IMPACT: • Reduces bloat/unnecessary items in the taskbar.
; IMPACT: • Does not uninstall anything: it's just a UI hider.
; RISK: • If someone actually uses Meet Now, they will have to access it another way.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Clean taskbar setting: very safe
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer]
"HideSCAMeetNow"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• System interface • Disable Widgets (System)
; ID: Taskbar_DisableWidgets
; DESC: Completely disables Windows Widgets / News & Interests.
; IMPACT: • Blocks the News & Interests functionality via a system policy.
; IMPACT: • Removes the Widgets icon from the taskbar for the user.
; IMPACT: • Prevents web widgets (weather, news, interests) from being displayed, loaded, and executed.
; IMPACT: • Reduces network activity, background processes, and UI clutter.
; RISK: • Loss of access to Windows widgets (weather, news, quick info).
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Anti-widget/Clean UI/Anti-web content settings: ideal combination for permanently removing widgets, very clean and long-lasting.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Dsh]
"AllowNewsAndInterests"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar] • System interface • Disable Widgets icon (visual)
; ID: Taskbar_DisableWidgetsIcon
; DESC: Completely disables Windows Widgets / News & Interests.
; IMPACT: • Blocks the News & Interests functionality via a system policy.
; IMPACT: • Removes the Widgets icon from the taskbar for the user.
; IMPACT: • Prevents web widgets (weather, news, interests) from being displayed, loaded, and executed.
; IMPACT: • Reduces network activity, background processes, and UI clutter.
; RISK: • Loss of access to Windows widgets (weather, news, quick info).
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Anti-widget/Clean UI/Anti-web content settings: ideal combination for permanently removing widgets, very clean and long-lasting.
; RESTART: EXPLORER																			
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"TaskbarDa"=dword:00000000	
																						
; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• Built-in apps • Disable Chat/Teams Icon
; ID: Taskbar_DisableChatIcon
; DESC: Completely disables the Windows Chat/Teams icon.
; IMPACT: • Completely hides the Chat icon and Teams integration.
; IMPACT: • Does not prevent the installation or manual use of Teams.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Teams-related UI integration and promotional elements from appearing in the taskbar.
; RISK: • Direct access to Teams from the taskbar is removed.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Debloat/Clean UI setting: Cleans the taskbar by removing the Chat icon.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Windows Chat]
"ChatIcon"=dword:00000003
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"TaskbarMn"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• Buttons • Disable Task View icon
; ID: Taskbar_DisableTaskViewIcon
; DESC: Hides the "Task View" button in the taskbar.
; IMPACT: • Removes the Task View icon (Win+Tab remains available).
; IMPACT: • Reduces taskbar clutter.
; IMPACT: • No impact on performance, only visual/ergonomics.
; RISK: • No risk.
; NOTE: Minimal UI setting / clean taskbar: useful for a cleaner taskbar.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"ShowTaskViewButton"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• Built-in apps • Disable the Copilot icon
; ID: Taskbar_DisableCopilotIcon
; DESC: Hides the Copilot button in the taskbar.
; IMPACT: • Does not uninstall Copilot: it primarily affects the interface.
; IMPACT: • Makes the taskbar cleaner.
; RISK: • No risk.
; RISK: • Copilot remains accessible through other means if Windows has enabled it (depending on the version).
; NOTE: UI/debloat setting: perfect for a minimalist taskbar.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"ShowCopilotButton"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• Options • Added "End Task" option to right click
; ID: Taskbar_AddedEndTask
; DESC: Enables the "End Task" option directly from the taskbar.
; IMPACT: • Adds the "End Task" entry to the right•click menu for open applications in the taskbar.
; IMPACT: • Allows you to force-close a frozen application without opening the Task Manager.
; RISK: • No impact on system stability or security.
; NOTE: Productivity tweak / quick troubleshooting: provides immediate access to force-close apps, very convenient for everyday use.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced\TaskbarDeveloperSettings]
"TaskbarEndTask"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• Layout • Left Alignment of Icons
; ID: Taskbar_AlignmentIconsLeft
; DESC: Aligns taskbar icons to the left (classic style).
; IMPACT: • Places taskbar icons on the left (classic behavior, like Windows 10).
; IMPACT: • Only changes the visual layout of the taskbar.
; RISK: • No risk.
; NOTE: Ergonomics/habits setting: ideal for restoring a familiar and efficient layout.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"TaskbarAl"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• Layout • Center Alignment of Icons
; ID: Taskbar_AlignmentIconsCenter
; DESC: Aligns taskbar icons to the center.
; IMPACT: • Places taskbar icons on the center.
; IMPACT: • Only changes the visual layout of the taskbar.
; RISK: • No risk.
; NOTE: Ergonomics/habits setting: ideal for restoring a familiar and efficient layout.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"TaskbarAl"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• Layout • Disable Window Grouping
; ID: Taskbar_DisableWindowGrouping
; DESC: Disables window grouping in the taskbar.								   
; IMPACT: • Displays each window separately, even for the same application.
; IMPACT: • Makes it easier to identify and directly access each open window.
; IMPACT: • Improves productivity when multiple instances are used (Explorer, browsers, editors).
; RISK: • Taskbar becomes more cluttered if many windows are open.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Ergonomics/power-user setting: prioritizes clarity and direct access to windows over compact aesthetics.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"TaskbarGlomLevel"=dword:00000002

; KORSiOS - [Taskbar]• Notifications • Disable notification badges/dots on icons
; ID: Taskbar_DisableNotificationBadges
; DESC: Disables badges (small indicators) on taskbar icons.
; IMPACT: • Removes dots/counters (e.g., message count) on pinned apps.														 
; IMPACT: • Reduces visual distractions.
; RISK: • You will no longer see counters/alerts directly on the icons.
; RISK: • You may miss "silent" notifications (e.g., Mail, Teams, Messaging).
; NOTE: UI tweak/distraction: a very good tweak to avoid visual distractions
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"TaskbarBadges"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [BitLocker]Block automatic device encryption
; DESC: Prevents Windows from automatically enabling device encryption.
; IMPACT: • Blocks silent activation (Device Encryption) on compatible machines.
; IMPACT: • Avoids automatic activation and key backup to a Microsoft account.
; RISK: • The disk will remain unencrypted if BitLocker is not manually enabled.
; NOTE: • Control setting: gives the choice when/how to encrypt.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\BitLocker]
"PreventDeviceEncryption"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [BitLocker]Allow automatic device encryption
; DESC: Allows Windows to enable automatic encryption if eligible.
; IMPACT: • Restores default behavior (if the device is compatible).
; RISK: • Windows can automatically encrypt depending on the context (MS account, hardware).
; NOTE: • Use only if you are looking for the stock behavior of Windows.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\BitLocker]
"PreventDeviceEncryption"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [BitLocker]Hardened configuration FVE (TPM + PIN + XTS-AES 256)
; DESC: Tightens BitLocker policy: TPM required, PIN required, XTS-AES 256 encryption, Secure Boot integrity.
; IMPACT: • Enhances startup protection (TPM+PIN).
; IMPACT: • Defines the recommended encryption method XTS-AES 256.
; IMPACT: • Increases resistance against offline/theft attacks.
; RISK: • If PIN forgotten => recovery required (recovery key).
; RISK: • May be too strict for some PCs (TPM missing / automated usage).
; NOTE: Advanced security pack: ideal for laptops/professionals. Requires recovery key management.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\FVE]
"UseTPM"=dword:00000002
"UseTPMPIN"=dword:00000002
"UseTPMKey"=dword:00000001
"UseAdvancedStartup"=dword:00000001
"OSAllowSecureBootForIntegrity"=dword:00000001
"EncryptionMethodWithXtsOs"=dword:00000007
"EncryptionMethodWithXtsFdv"=dword:00000007
"EncryptionMethodWithXtsRdv"=dword:00000007
"OSRecovery"=dword:00000001
"OSRecoveryPassword"=dword:00000002
"OSRecoveryKey"=dword:00000002
"OSHideRecoveryPage"=dword:00000000
"FDVRecovery"=dword:00000001
"FDVRecoveryPassword"=dword:00000002
"FDVRecoveryKey"=dword:00000002
"RDVRecovery"=dword:00000001
"RDVRecoveryPassword"=dword:00000002
"RDVRecoveryKey"=dword:00000002

; KORSiOS - [BitLocker]Remove all BitLocker policies (FVE)
; DESC: Completely removes the BitLocker Policy Key (FVE) and all its associated configurations.
; IMPACT: • Removes all BitLocker policies configured via the registry.
; IMPACT: • Windows reverts to default behavior (not configured by policy).
; IMPACT: • Removes TPM/PIN/encryption method requirements.
; IMPACT: • Does not affect the current encryption state of an already encrypted disk.
; RISK: • If BitLocker was configured with strict requirements, these disappear.
; RISK: • In an enterprise environment, this may conflict with GPO domains.
; RISK: • The behavior again becomes dependent on the Windows edition (Home/Pro) and UI settings.
; NOTE: • Clean rollback method: preferable to setting all values ​​to 0.
; NOTE: • Do NOT disable BitLocker if it is already active on a volume.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[-HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\FVE]

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• CEIP • Disable Customer Experience Improvement Program
; ID: CEIP_DisableCustomerExperience
; DESC: Globally disables the Microsoft Customer Experience Improvement Program (CEIP/SQM).
; IMPACT: • Cuts off participation in the Customer Experience Improvement Program for several Windows components:
; IMPACT: - Windows (SQMClient)
; IMPACT: - App-V
; IMPACT: - Internet Explorer (SQM)
; IMPACT: - Messenger Client
; IMPACT: - Unattend/OOBE settings
; IMPACT: • Reduces the sending of no essential usage/diagnostic data to Microsoft.
; IMPACT: • Contributes to a more privacy-conscious/low-profile configuration.
; RISK: • Support/diagnostics: less "feedback" data sent, therefore potentially less useful for Microsoft in the event of a global analysis (but virtually no impact on the user).
; RISK: • No system risk
; NOTE: Privacy setting: disables historical "CEIP" telemetry (SQM). No direct performance gain, but a quieter and more consistent Windows experience.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\SQMClient\Windows]
"CEIPEnable"=dword:00000000
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\SQMClient\Windows]
"CEIPEnable"=dword:00000000
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\AppV\CEIP]
"CEIPEnable"=dword:00000000
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Internet Explorer\SQM]
"DisableCustomerImprovementProgram"=dword:00000001
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Messenger\Client]
"CEIP"=dword:00000002
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\UnattendSettings\SQMClient]
"CEIPEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Assistant • Disable Cortana
; ID: Privacy_DisableCortana
; DESC: Disables Cortana in Windows Search.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Cortana from being integrated into the search bar and related functions.
; IMPACT: • Windows Search remains functional for files, applications, and settings, without the voice assistant.
; IMPACT: • Reduces background activity related to Cortana and associated cloud services.
; RISK: • Loss of Cortana functionality.
; RISK: • No impact on the stability, security, or performance of regular search.
; NOTE: Debloat/Privacy setting: maintains efficient local search while removing the voice assistant.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Windows Search]
"AllowCortana"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Data • Disable Online Speech Recognition
; ID: Privacy_Speech
; DESC: Disables online (cloud) speech recognition permission for the user.
; IMPACT: • Disables dictation/voice command services that use the Microsoft cloud.
; IMPACT: • Reduces the potential sending of voice/text samples to Microsoft servers.
; IMPACT: • Does not necessarily disable offline speech recognition if available (varies by language/build).
; RISK: • Voice dictation may become less accurate or unavailable if it relied on the cloud.
; RISK: • Some voice input features may display a message prompting you to enable online speech recognition.
; NOTE: "Strong" privacy setting: zero cloud for voice (work PC, offline, clean gaming).
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Speech_OneCore\Settings\OnlineSpeechPrivacy]
"HasAccepted"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Data • Disable Text Input Personalization (TIPC)
; ID: Privacy_Tipc
; DESC: Disables Text Input Personalization/collection features for the user.
; IMPACT: • Disables TIPC (Text Input Personalization/collection).
; IMPACT: • Reduces Windows' automatic learning of your typing style.
; IMPACT: • May reduce some cloud interactions if they were related to personalization.
; RISK: • Input suggestions may be less relevant.
; RISK: • Autocorrect may be less effective.
; RISK: • Some touch keyboard (tablet) features may be less "intelligent".
; NOTE: "Input" privacy setting: useful for minimizing input personalization and Windows learning.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Input\TIPC]
"Enabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Assistant • Disable Copilot
; ID: Privacy_DisableCopilot
; DESC: Disables Windows Copilot for the user.
; IMPACT: • Prevents access to Copilot (sidebar, shortcuts, UI integration).
; IMPACT: • Removes interface elements and calls associated with Copilot.
; IMPACT: • Reduces cloud/AI-dependent functionality.
; RISK: • Loss of Copilot functionality (integrated AI assistance).
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Privacy/UI minimalism setting: disables Copilot for a cleaner, more predictable Windows experience.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\WindowsCopilot]
"TurnOffWindowsCopilot"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Data • Disable application compatibility cache
; ID: Privacy_DisableAppCompCache
; DESC: Disables the application compatibility cache (AppCompat Cache / Shim cache).
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from maintaining the application runtime cache used for compatibility and execution tracking.
; IMPACT: • Reduces activity related to the AppCompat / shim engine mechanisms.
; IMPACT: • May limit some automatic compatibility optimizations.
; IMPACT: • Slightly reduces the trace left by program execution.
; RISK: • Some older applications may lose automatic compatibility adjustments.
; RISK: • Windows diagnostic/forensic tools are less informative.
; RISK: • No impact on overall system stability.
; NOTE: Anti-compat tracking/privacy setting: useful for a clean system without automatic shims.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\AppCompatCache]
"AppCompatCacheEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security] Disable Sensor Access
; DESC: Blocks access to Windows sensors.
; IMPACT: • May disable access to certain hardware sensors.
; IMPACT: • Typically affects sensors such as:
; IMPACT: - Location (position sensor)
; IMPACT: - Motion/orientation sensor (tablets / 2 in 1s)
; IMPACT: - Ambient light sensors (auto-brightness)
; IMPACT: • Enhances privacy by preventing the sensor from being used by Windows and/or apps.
; RISK: • May break sensor-dependent functions:
; RISK: - Auto-rotate screen (Surface / tablet)
; RISK: - Auto-brightness
; RISK: - "Find My Device" function (if location sensor is present)
; RISK: - Some apps (weather, maps, camera, etc.)
; NOTE: Advanced privacy setting: very useful on laptops/tablets if you want to block sensors at the system level.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Sensor\Overrides\{BFA794E4-F964-4FDB-90F6-51056BFE4B44}]
"SensorPermissionState"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Permissions • Disable Location
; ID: Privacy_DisableLocation
; DESC: Disables location access for all Windows applications.
; IMPACT: • Forces the "Deny" value for location capability at the system level.
; IMPACT: • Prevents applications (UWP/Store and affected Windows components) from accessing geolocation data.
; IMPACT: • Apps using location (Weather, Maps, location-based services) will no longer receive location data.
; RISK: • Degraded functionality for location-dependent applications.
; RISK: • No risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: Privacy setting: disables geolocation globally. Ideal for a privacy-oriented system, but should be avoided if apps actually need location data.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\CapabilityAccessManager\ConsentStore\location]
"Value"="Deny"
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\lfsvc\Service\Configuration]
"Status"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security] • Permissions • Disable automatic updates for offline maps
; DESC: Disables automatic updates for Windows offline maps (Maps).
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from automatically downloading map updates.
; IMPACT: • Reduces background network activity related to offline maps.
; IMPACT: • Reduces disk writing related to Maps updates.
; IMPACT: • Useful on PCs where you never use offline maps.
; RISK: • If you use offline maps, they may become outdated without automatic updates.
; RISK: • You will need to update manually via Settings / Maps if necessary.
; NOTE: Privacy setting + background clean: useful for limiting invisible downloads and unnecessary tasks.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\Maps]
"AutoUpdateEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Data • Disabled Telemetry & Diagnostic Collection
; ID: Privacy_DisableTelemetry
; DESC: Disables advanced Windows telemetry and diagnostic collection.
; IMPACT: • Blocks system telemetry and usage data collection.
; IMPACT: • Disables extended diagnostic logging and dump collection.
; IMPACT: • Suppresses Microsoft feedback notifications.
; IMPACT: • Disables Application Compatibility Analysis (AIT).
; IMPACT: • Significantly reduces communication with Microsoft.
; IMPACT: • Reduces background service activity.
; IMPACT: • Enhances overall system privacy.
; RISK: • Less accurate Microsoft support: less data sent in case of a bug.
; RISK: • Some intelligent diagnostic features may be limited.
; RISK: • No risk of negative stability or performance.
; NOTE: Privacy/System Cleanliness setting: This is the core of a Windows system without telemetry.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\DataCollection]
"AllowTelemetry"=dword:00000000
"AllowBuildPreview"=dword:00000000
"LimitDiagnosticLogCollection"=dword:00000001
"LimitDumpCollection"=dword:00000001
"AllowCommercialDataPipeline"=dword:00000000
"AllowDeviceNameInTelemetry"=dword:00000000
"DisableTelemetryOptInChangeNotification"=dword:00000001
"DisableTelemetryOptInSettingsUx"=dword:00000001
"DoNotShowFeedbackNotifications"=dword:00000001
"LimitEnhancedDiagnosticDataWindowsAnalytics"=dword:00000000
"AllowBuildPreview"=dword:00000000
"LimitDiagnosticLogCollection"=dword:00000001
"LimitDumpCollection"=dword:00000001

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\DataCollection]
"AllowTelemetry"=dword:00000000

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\PolicyManager\default\System\AllowTelemetry]
"value"=dword:00000000

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\CPSS\DevicePolicy\AllowTelemetry]
"value"=dword:00000000

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\CPSS\Store\AllowTelemetry]
"Value"=dword:00000000

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\DataCollection]
"AllowTelemetry"=dword:00000000

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\AppCompatFlags]
"AITEnable"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Data • Disable Autologgers Telemetry (WMI)
; ID: Privacy_DisableWMI
; DESC: Disables several WMI trackers (Autologgers) related to telemetry and Windows diagnostics.
; IMPACT: • Prevents the automatic startup of Diagtrack-Listener, SQMLogger and SetupPlatformTel trackers.
; IMPACT: • Reduces the collection of diagnostic events in the background.
; IMPACT: • Limits certain writing related to telemetry logs.
; IMPACT: • Reduces activity associated with the Connected User Experience (DiagTrack) service.
; RISK: • May reduce diagnostic capabilities in case of system problems or crashes.
; RISK: • May impact certain analysis mechanisms during Windows upgrades.
; RISK: • Windows may reactivate these trackers after a major update.
; NOTE: Advanced telemetry hardening setting: useful for strict privacy environments.
; NOTE: Very low performance impact, primarily a confidentiality effect.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\ControlSet001\Control\WMI\Autologger\Diagtrack-Listener]
"Start"=dword:00000000

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\ControlSet001\Control\WMI\Autologger\SQMLogger]
"Start"=dword:00000000

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\ControlSet001\Control\WMI\Autologger\SetupPlatformTel]
"Start"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Advertising • Disable Advertising ID
; ID: Privacy_DisableAdvertisingID
; DESC: Disables the Windows Advertising ID for the user.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows and apps from using a unique Advertising ID.
; IMPACT: • Reduces ad targeting and personalization based on user activity.
; IMPACT: • Limits data sharing for marketing purposes.
; RISK: • Less relevant ads in some apps (Store, UWP apps).
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Privacy setting: Turns off ad tracking at the Windows level for a more privacy-friendly experience.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\AdvertisingInfo]
"Enabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Advertising • Disable Personalized Content / Usage•Based Suggestions
; ID: Privacy_DisablePersonalizedContent
; DESC: Disables personalized experiences based on diagnostic data.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from using diagnostic data to personalize content, tips, and recommendations.
; IMPACT: • Reduces cloud personalization and user data processing.
; IMPACT: • Makes the Windows experience more neutral and predictable.
; RISK: • Fewer suggestions tailored to personal use.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Privacy setting / Streamlined UX: Limits the use of diagnostic data for personalization.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Privacy]
"TailoredExperiencesWithDiagnosticDataEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• History • Turn off Activity History (Timeline)
; ID: Privacy_ActivityHistoryOff
; DESC: Completely disables Windows Activity History and Timeline.
; IMPACT: • Disables Timeline and Activity History.
; IMPACT: • Prevents local activity from being saved.
; IMPACT: • Blocks activity from being sent to the Microsoft cloud.
; IMPACT: • Removes activity synchronization between devices and accounts.
; RISK: • Loss of Timeline and cross-device activity resumption.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Privacy/Sobriety setting: Turns off activity tracking and cloud synchronization for a more discreet and controlled Windows experience.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\System]
"EnableActivityFeed"=dword:00000000
"PublishUserActivities"=dword:00000000
"UploadUserActivities"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Data • Disable DiagTrack service
; ID: Privacy_DisableDiagTrack
; DESC: Disables the Connected User Experiences and Telemetry (DiagTrack) service.
; IMPACT: • Stops telemetry collection, diagnostics, and sending usage data to Microsoft.
; IMPACT: • Reduces background CPU, disk, and network activity.
; IMPACT: • Improves privacy and consistency with other anti-telemetry settings (CEIP, DataCollection).
; RISK: • Loss of some automatic diagnostics used by Microsoft for fault analysis.
; RISK: • May limit the effectiveness of some Microsoft support tools.
; RISK: • No risk to daily system stability.
; NOTE: Privacy/anti-telemetry setting: classic and very common, considered a basic feature in any well-maintained Windows configuration.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\DiagTrack]
"Start"=dword:00000004

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• History • Disable Clipboard History & Cloud Sync
; ID: Privacy_DisableClipboardHistory
; DESC: Disables clipboard history and cross-device synchronization.
; IMPACT: • Blocks the saving of copy history (Win+V).
; IMPACT: • Prevents cloud synchronization of the clipboard between Microsoft devices.
; IMPACT: • Reduces local collection of copied data.
; IMPACT: • Enhances clipboard privacy and predictability.
; RISK: • Loss of clipboard history functionality.
; RISK: • No synchronization between PCs.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or performance.
; NOTE: Privacy/data security setting: useful on professional or sensitive machines. Removes a convenient but intrusive feature.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\System]
"AllowClipboardHistory"=dword:00000000
"AllowCrossDeviceClipboard"=dword:00000000
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Clipboard]
"EnableClipboardHistory"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Data • Disable input personalization (inking/typing)
; ID: Privacy_DisableInputPerso
; DESC: Disables the collection of input data (text, ink, contacts) for personalization.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from recording keystrokes, handwriting, and contact data for local AI.
; IMPACT: • Disables personalized learning of the predictive keyboard and handwriting.
; IMPACT: • Reduces the collection of data related to user input.
; IMPACT: • Improves privacy without impacting basic keyboard functions.
; RISK: • Less intelligent text prediction and suggestions.
; RISK: • Loss of keyboard/typing personalization.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or performance.
; NOTE: Input privacy setting: recommended to limit all behavioral data collection.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\InputPersonalization]
"RestrictImplicitTextCollection"=dword:00000001
"RestrictImplicitInkCollection"=dword:00000001
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\InputPersonalization\TrainedDataStore]
"HarvestContacts"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Personalization • Decline Windows Personalization Policy
; ID: Privacy_Perso
; DESC: Marks the personalization privacy policy as not accepted for the user.
; IMPACT: • Reduces certain Windows personalizations based on user activity.
; IMPACT: • Strengthens privacy by preventing the implicit activation of certain personalization services.
; RISK: • Some Windows suggestions may become less relevant (or disappear).
; RISK: • Some Settings pages may require re-acceptance after an update or Microsoft login.
; NOTE: "Global" privacy setting: useful for a clean setup where you want to minimize Microsoft recommendations and personalization.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Personalization\Settings]
"AcceptedPrivacyPolicy"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Permissions • Disable "Contacts" access for apps
; ID: Privacy_DisableContactsAccess
; DESC: Disables access to contacts for Windows applications.
; IMPACT: • Prevents modern apps (UWP/Store) from accessing your contacts.
; IMPACT: • Reduces the sharing of personal data.
; IMPACT: • Primarily impacts Microsoft apps (Mail, People, Teams, etc.).
; RISK: • Some apps will no longer be able to automatically import your contacts.
; RISK: • May interfere with Mail/Calendar/Teams integration.
; RISK: • No system risk.
; NOTE: Privacy setting: very good if you don't use the Microsoft Contacts ecosystem.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\CapabilityAccessManager\ConsentStore\contacts]
"Value"="Deny"

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Permissions • Disable Calendar Access for Apps
; ID: Privacy_DisableCalendarAccess
; DESC: Disables calendar access for Windows applications.
; IMPACT: • Prevents modern apps (UWP/Store) from accessing the calendar.
; IMPACT: • Reduces the sharing of personal data.
; IMPACT: • Primarily impacts Microsoft apps (Mail, Calendar, Teams, etc.).
; RISK: • Some apps will no longer be able to display/sync your calendar.
; RISK: • May break features such as reminders, Teams integration, and calendar widgets.
; RISK: • No risk to stability.
; NOTE: Strong privacy setting: perfect if you don't use the Windows calendar. Otherwise, it's best to leave it on "Allow" or "Ask".
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\CapabilityAccessManager\ConsentStore\appointments]
"Value"="Deny"

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Permissions • Disable SMS access for apps
; ID: Privacy_DisableSMSAccess
; DESC: Disables access to chat/messaging features for Windows applications.
; IMPACT: • Prevents modern apps (UWP/Store) from accessing chat capabilities.
; IMPACT: • Reduces the sharing of personal data.
; IMPACT: • Reduces Microsoft integrations (Windows Chat, integrated Teams, etc.).
; RISK: • Some apps will no longer be able to access certain messaging features linked to the Microsoft account.
; RISK: • May break features such as reminders, Teams integration, and calendar widgets.
; RISK: • No risk to stability.
; NOTE: Privacy + debloat setting: useful if you want to remove all Windows chat integration.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\CapabilityAccessManager\ConsentStore\chat]
"Value"="Deny"

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Permissions • Disable Find My Device
; ID: Privacy_DisableFindMyDevice
; DESC: Disables location and synchronization of "Find My Device".
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from transmitting the PC's location to the Microsoft account.
; IMPACT: • Disables the remote tracking feature in case of loss/theft.
; IMPACT: • Reduces communication related to geolocation.
; IMPACT: • Improves privacy.
; RISK: • Unable to use the Find My Device feature from the Microsoft account.
; RISK: • Loss of a convenient anti-theft mechanism.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or performance.
; NOTE: Hardware privacy/anti-tracking setting: good choice for a desktop PC or controlled environment. Less recommended for a mobile device.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Settings\FindMyDevice]
"LocationSyncEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Advertising • Disable Spotlight
; ID: Privacy_DisableSpotlight
; DESC: Completely disables Windows Spotlight and personalized/suggested content for the user.
; IMPACT: • Disables Windows Spotlight.
; IMPACT: • Prevents the use of Spotlight for Business.
; IMPACT: • Blocks third-party app suggestions.
; IMPACT: • Prevents personalization based on diagnostic data.
; IMPACT: • Static user experience, without cloud content or promotions.
; RISK: • Loss of dynamic lock screen images and info (Spotlight).
; RISK: • Fewer recommendations for novice users.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Anti-ad/privacy/clean UX setting: Completely disables Spotlight and cloud personalization for a clean, quiet, and predictable Windows experience.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\CloudContent]
"ConfigureWindowsSpotlight"=dword:00000002
"IncludeEnterpriseSpotlight"=dword:00000000
"DisableThirdPartySuggestions"=dword:00000001
"DisableTailoredExperiencesWithDiagnosticData"=dword:00000001
"DisableWindowsSpotlightFeatures"=dword:00000001
"DisableWindowsSpotlightWindowsWelcomeExperience"=dword:00000001
"DisableWindowsSpotlightOnActionCenter"=dword:00000001
"DisableWindowsSpotlightOnSettings"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Permissions • Disable microphone (apps)
; ID: Privacy_DisableMicrophone
; DESC: Blocks microphone access for applications (Windows permissions).
; IMPACT: • Prevents UWP/Store apps and some modern Windows apps from using the microphone.
; IMPACT: • Significantly improves privacy.
; RISK: • The microphone may no longer work in:
; RISK: - Discord (depending on version/configuration)
; RISK: - Teams / Zoom / Store apps
; RISK: - Windows Voice Dictation
; RISK: • Some Win32 apps may partially bypass this depending on their audio access methods.
; RISK: • May generate "microphone not detected" bugs.
; NOTE: Strong privacy setting: excellent if you don't use the microphone, but avoid it on a PC where you use voice communication.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\CapabilityAccessManager\ConsentStore\microphone]
"Value"="Deny"

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Permissions • Disable webcam (apps)
; ID: Privacy_DisableWebcam
; DESC: Blocks webcam access for applications (Windows permissions).
; IMPACT: • Disables camera permission at the Windows level.
; IMPACT: • Prevents modern apps (UWP/Store) and some software from capturing via the webcam.
; RISK: • The camera will no longer work in:
; RISK: - Teams / Zoom / Skype
; RISK: - Windows Camera apps
; RISK: - Discord (depending on version)
; RISK: • May cause "camera unavailable" errors until re-enabled.
; NOTE: Strong privacy setting: perfect if you don't use the webcam. Otherwise, leave it on "Ask" or "Allow".
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\CapabilityAccessManager\ConsentStore\webcam]
"Value"="Deny"

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Data • Disable Windows Feedback Requests (SIUF)
; ID: Privacy_DisableFeedback
; DESC: Disables Windows feedback requests (“Give us your feedback”).
; IMPACT: • Sets the frequency and duration of SIUF requests to 0.
; IMPACT: • Greatly reduces/eliminates Microsoft feedback notifications.
; RISK: • Disables (or significantly reduces) Windows feedback requests.
; RISK: • No system risk.
; NOTE: Privacy setting: does not disable all telemetry, only the “feedback” portion.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Siuf\Rules]
"NumberOfSIUFInPeriod"=dword:00000000
"PeriodInNanoSeconds"=qword:0000000000000000
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\DataCollection]
"DoNotShowFeedbackNotifications"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Lock Screen • Disable Camera Access on the Lock Screen
; ID: Privacy_DisableCameraAccessLock
; DESC: Prevents camera use from the Windows lock screen.
; IMPACT: • Disables the camera shortcut/access available before login.
; IMPACT: • Reduces camera usage without being logged in.
; RISK: • The camera will no longer be usable from the lock screen (if you were using this feature).
; RISK: • No impact once logged into Windows.
; NOTE: Clean and safe security setting. Especially useful on laptops/tablets/Surfaces.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Personalization]
"NoLockScreenCamera"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Lock Screen • Disable Slideshow on Lock Screen
; ID: Privacy_DisableSlideshowLock
; DESCRIPTION: Disables the image slideshow on the Windows lock screen.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from using a rotating image folder on the lock screen.
; IMPACT: • Reduces the risk of unintentionally exposing personal images on a shared PC.
; IMPACT: • Prevents certain disk/SSD accesses related to image loading (very low performance impact).
; IMPACT: • Enhances the "minimal lock screen" mode (cleaner and more minimalist).
; RISK: • The slideshow on the lock screen will no longer function.
; RISK: • No impact on Windows Spotlight (if enabled), unless Spotlight was configured as a slideshow.
; NOTE: Simple security and privacy setting. Works well in a "LockScreen Hardening" package.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Personalization]
"NoLockScreenSlideshow"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Lockdown • Disable Automatic Restart Sign-On (ARSO)
; ID: Privacy_DisableAutoRestart
; DESC: Prevents Windows from automatically reconnecting after a restart to complete updates.
; IMPACT: • Disables the ARSO (Automatic Restart Sign-On) feature.
; IMPACT: • Windows will no longer be able to use your credentials to automatically log you in after a reboot.
; IMPACT: • Updates will still complete, but some steps will wait until the session is unlocked.
; IMPACT: • Reduces the risk of a session opening on its own while you are away.
; RISK: • After some updates, Windows may require manual login to complete.
; RISK: • May give the impression that "Windows took longer to finish an update" (because it waits for login).
; NOTE: A clean and recommended security setting. This is the equivalent of disabling "Use my login information to automatically complete setup...".
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\System]
"DisableAutomaticRestartSignOn"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• Traces • Clear “Recent Documents” on Logoff
; ID: Privacy_ClearRecentDoc
; DESC: Automatically clears the recent file history each time you log off.
; IMPACT: • Deletes the “Recent Documents” list on logout/logoff.
; IMPACT: • Clears the history displayed in:
; IMPACT: - Start Menu
; IMPACT: - File Explorer
; IMPACT: - Jump Lists
; IMPACT: • Reduces usage traces on a shared PC.
; IMPACT: • Reduces the risk of a session opening on its own while you are away.
; RISK: • You lose the convenience of quick access to recently opened files.
; RISK: • Some apps that rely on Windows history will receive fewer suggestions.
; NOTE: Privacy setting on shared/work PC. On a personal PC, it's a choice between convenience and privacy.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer]
"ClearRecentDocsOnExit"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Privacy / Security]• NVIDIA • Disable the NVIDIA panel telemetry preference
; ID: Privacy_Nvidia
; DESC: Sets the NVIDIA Control Panel (NVControlPanel2) Opt-in/Opt-out preference to 0.
; IMPACT: • Disables membership in collection/sharing options associated with the NVIDIA panel.
; IMPACT: • Reduces certain communications related to NVIDIA panel user preferences.
; IMPACT: • Does not affect GPU performance or drivers.
; IMPACT: • Does not impact GeForce Experience (separate component).
; RISK: • May disable certain recommendations or connected features of the NVIDIA control panel.
; RISK: • Limited effect if other NVIDIA components (e.g., GeForce Experience) are installed.
; NOTE: Light privacy setting: useful if you want to minimize all NVIDIA telemetry on the control panel side.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\NVIDIA Corporation\NVControlPanel2\Client]
"OptInOrOutPreference"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Cloud] Disable cloud•optimized content
; ID: Cloud_DisableCloudContent
; DESC: Disables personalized experiences and cloud-optimized content in Windows.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from using diagnostic data to personalize the experience.
; IMPACT: • Blocks dynamic content from the cloud.
; IMPACT: • More neutral interface, less dependent on Microsoft online services.
; RISK: • Less automatic personalization.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Clean privacy/UX setting: Windows becomes more discreet and predictable, ideal for a controlled setup without promotional content.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\CloudContent]
"DisableTailoredExperiencesWithDiagnosticData"=dword:00000001
"DisableCloudOptimizedContent"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Content Delivery Manager] Complete Disable: Sponsored Content / Suggestions / Recommended Apps
; ID: Content_Disable
; DESC: Disables the entire Windows sponsored content / suggestions / recommended apps system.
; IMPACT: • Turns off Windows Spotlight, sponsored content, app suggestions, and silent app installations.
; IMPACT: • Disables soft landing and recommendation mechanisms.
; IMPACT: • Disables rotating images on the lock screen.
; IMPACT: • The system becomes static, predictable, and devoid of promotional content.
; RISK: • Loss of visual features such as dynamic lock screen images (Spotlight).
; RISK: • Fewer discoveries/suggestions for novice users.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Anti•bloat/anti•ad/clean UX setting: removes all promotional and automated Windows content for a clean and controlled experience.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\ContentDeliveryManager]
"ContentDeliveryAllowed"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContentEnabled"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContent-310093Enabled"=dword:00000000
"SoftLandingEnabled"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContent-338389Enabled"=dword:00000000
"SilentInstalledAppsEnabled"=dword:00000000
"PreInstalledAppsEnabled"=dword:00000000
"PreInstalledAppsEverEnabled"=dword:00000000
"OemPreInstalledAppsEnabled"=dword:00000000
"FeatureManagementEnabled"=dword:00000000
"RemediationRequired"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContent-314559Enabled"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContent-280815Enabled"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContent-314563Enabled"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContent-202914Enabled"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContent-338387Enabled"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContent-280810Enabled"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContent-280811Enabled"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContent-338388Enabled"=dword:00000000
"SubscribedContent-338393Enabled"=dword:00000000
"RotatingLockScreenEnabled"=dword:00000000
"RotatingLockScreenOverlayEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [CPU / Scheduler] CPU: Prioritize foreground applications
; ID: CPU_PriorityForeground
; DESC: Adjusts CPU priority and time sharing to favor foreground applications over background tasks.
; IMPACT: • Improved responsiveness of interactive applications.
; IMPACT: • More CPU resources allocated to the foreground, at the expense of services/background processes.
; RISK: • Background tasks (indexing, backups, resource-intensive services) may be slightly less responsive.
; RISK: • On some highly multitasking workloads (server, rendering, VMs), this setting may be counterproductive.
; RISK: • Low risk and easily reversible.
; NOTE: Classic "desktop/gaming" setting: it makes the system more responsive during active use, without critical impact, but is not ideal for server use or intensive background computing.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\PriorityControl]
"Win32PrioritySeparation"=dword:00000026

; KORSiOS - [CPU / Scheduler] CPU: Favor foreground boost
; ID: CPU_ForegroundBoost
; DESC: Increases the CPU priority bonus given to the foreground application.
; IMPACT: • Strengthens the priority of interactive processes.
; IMPACT: • Improves the smoothness of the active application (game, software, UI).
; IMPACT: • Reduces CPU competition with background tasks.
; RISK: • Background tasks may be slowed down under heavy load.
; RISK: • Negligible impact on a modern multi-core PC.
; NOTE: Interactivity/gaming setting: consistent with foreground performance optimization.
; NOTE: Complements the "CPU: Prioritize foreground applications" tweak well.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\PriorityControl]
"ForegroundBoost"=dword:00000002

; KORSiOS - [CPU / Scheduler] CPU: Disable CPU Reserve
; ID: CPU_DisableCPUReserve
; DESC: Removes the CPU reserve that Windows keeps by default for background multimedia tasks (20%)
; IMPACT: • Tells Windows to no longer reserve a percentage of CPU for MMCSS services.
; IMPACT: • Active applications (games, real-time software) can use 100% of CPU resources if necessary.
; IMPACT: • Improves responsiveness and performance under heavy load, especially in gaming.
; RISK: • Background multimedia tasks (audio, video, secondary streaming) may become less prioritized under heavy CPU load.
; RISK: • On some machines, this may cause minor audio glitches if the CPU is saturated at 100%.
; RISK: • Low risk on high-performance desktop PCs, more noticeable on modest configurations.
; NOTE: Typical performance/gaming setting: Windows no longer allocates CPU resources and allows the main application to use all available power.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Multimedia\SystemProfile]
"SystemResponsiveness"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• Media • Disable AutoRun
; ID: Explorer_DisableAutoRun
; DESC: Completely disables AutoRun for all types of drives.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from automatically launching programs when media (USB, CD/DVD, etc.) is inserted.
; IMPACT: • Enhances security by blocking auto-launching scripts or executables.
; RISK: • No negative impact on system performance or stability.
; NOTE: Recommended security setting; it eliminates a common source of infection while remaining completely transparent in daily use.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer]
"NoDriveTypeAutoRun"=dword:000000ff

; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• Media • Disable AutoPlay (AutoPlay Suggestions window)
; ID: Explorer_DisableAutoPlay
; DESC: Disables AutoPlay when a device (USB, CD, etc.) is connected.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from automatically opening an action when you connect a device.
; IMPACT: • Enhances security and prevents automatic pop-ups.
; RISK: • No more "What do you want to do?" window.
; RISK: • No risk to stability
; NOTE: Security + convenience setting: a very good safe tweak to prevent automatic actions and limit the risks associated with removable media.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\AutoplayHandlers]
"DisableAutoplay"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• Performance • Launch folder windows in a separate process
; ID: Explorer_SeparateProcess
; DESC: Forces Windows Explorer to open folder windows in a separate process.
; IMPACT: • Enables the “Open folder windows in a separate process” option.
; IMPACT: • Each folder window can work independently from the main shell.
; IMPACT: • If an Explorer window crashes, it does not necessarily crash the entire taskbar/desktop.
; IMPACT: • Improves the overall stability of the interface in certain scenarios (heavy copy, unstable network).
; IMPACT: • Can reduce overall Explorer freezes in case of an error on a specific folder.
; RISK: • Slight increase in RAM usage (additional explorer.exe processes).
; RISK: • On small configurations (low RAM), noticeable memory impact if many windows open.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or security.
; NOTE: Power-user / transparency setting: essential to understand and master the file system.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"SeparateProcess"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• Explorer • Force Explorer to use GPU performance
; ID: Explorer_ExplorerGPU
; DESC: Forces Windows Explorer to use the high-performance GPU.
; IMPACT: • Tells Windows to use the most powerful available GPU (dedicated GPU if one exists).
; IMPACT: • May make the Explorer interface smoother.
; RISK: • Slightly higher power consumption.
; RISK: • No risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: Optimizes visual comfort/UI fluidity: useful on desktop PCs or powerful machines, optional on laptops if battery life is a priority.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\DirectX\UserGpuPreferences]
"C:\\Windows\\explorer.exe"="GpuPreference=2;"

; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• Display • Prevent the "shortcut to" text from being added when creating a shortcut
; ID: Explorer_DisableShortcutTo
; DESC: Prevents Windows from automatically adding the "Shortcut to" text when creating a new shortcut.
; IMPACT: • Created shortcuts are named directly filename.lnk instead of Shortcut to filename.
; IMPACT: • Only affects new shortcuts
; RISK: • No risk
; NOTE: Quality of life/ergonomics setting: it avoids the systematic manual renaming of shortcuts while maintaining their normal functionality.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer]
"Link"=hex:00,00,00,00

; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• View • Show file extensions
; ID: Explorer_ShowFilesExtension
; DESC: Displays all file extensions in Explorer.
; IMPACT: • Displays file extensions (.exe, .txt, .reg, etc.).
; RISK: • No impact on stability or security.
; NOTE: Power-user/transparency setting: essential for understanding and mastering the file system.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"HideFileExt"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• View • Show hidden files
; ID: Explorer_ShowHiddenFiles
; DESC: Displays all hidden and system files in Explorer.
