; RISK: • Loss of Home (recent files and frequently accessed folders) upon opening.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Productivity/power-user setting: prioritizes a direct, technical view of the directory tree.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"LaunchTo"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• History • Disable “Show recently opened items” in Jump Lists
; ID: Explorer_JumpLists
; DESC: Disables Jump Lists (recent items) in the Start menu and taskbar.
