; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• Navigation • Enable the status bar in File Explorer
; ID: Explorer_EnableStatusBar
; DESC: Displays the status bar at the bottom of Explorer (file information, size, selected items).
; IMPACT: • Enables the status bar at the bottom of Explorer windows.
; IMPACT: • Displays useful information:
; IMPACT: • Number of items in the folder
; IMPACT: • Number of selected items
; IMPACT: • Total size of selected items
; IMPACT: • Basic information about certain files (depending on type)
; IMPACT: • Improves productivity (sorting, copying, multiple selection).
; RISK: • Very slight visual change: Explorer displays an area at the bottom.
; RISK: • No system risk.
; NOTE: Productivity UI setting: useful if you frequently perform multiple selections, copying, sorting, renaming, etc.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"ShowStatusBar"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• Windows • Disable “Aero Peek” (desktop preview on hover)
; ID: Explorer_DisableAeroPeek
; DESC: Disables the desktop preview when you hover over the button on the far right of the taskbar.
; IMPACT: • Disables the “Peek” function: hovering prevents all windows from becoming transparent.
; IMPACT: • The “Show desktop” button (far right) remains usable by clicking, but without the preview on hover.
; IMPACT: • Reduces automatic visual effects (fewer distractions).
; IMPACT: • May prevent micro-lags on some configurations (weak GPUs / older PCs).
; IMPACT: • Limits unintentional display changes (accidental hovers).
; RISK: • Loss of the convenient quick desktop preview function without minimizing.
; RISK: • No system risk.
; NOTE: UI setting “comfort/anti-distract”: useful if you often accidentally hover over the right corner and makes the interface more stable and minimalist.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"DisablePreviewDesktop"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• Explorer • Disable network file thumbnails
; ID: Explorer_DisableNetworkThumbnails
; DESC: Disables thumbnails for files on network folders.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from generating image/video previews on network shares.
; IMPACT: • Reduces unnecessary network access when browsing in Explorer.
; IMPACT: • Improves the display speed of network folders.
; IMPACT: • Reduces the load on NAS/servers.
; RISK: • No visual preview of images/videos on the network.
; RISK: • Less comfortable browsing for multimedia content.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or security.
; NOTE: Network/NAS performance setting: useful when handling large network folders. Reduces Explorer slowdowns.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer]
"DisableThumbnailsOnNetworkFolders"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Explorer / UI]• Navigation • Disable automatic folder type detection
; ID: Explorer_FolderType
; DESC: Forces Windows not to apply an automatic folder pattern (Documents, Pictures, Videos, etc.).
; IMPACT: • Sets the global folder type to NotSpecified for all folders.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from analyzing the content and automatically changing the display.
; IMPACT: • Makes Explorer more consistent and predictable.
; RISK: • Loss of useful automatic optimizations for some folders.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Ergonomics setting / total control: prevents unexpected display changes in Explorer, highly recommended on a customized and consistent system.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Classes\Local Settings\Software\Microsoft\Windows\Shell\Bags\AllFolders\Shell]
"FolderType"="NotSpecified"

