; KORSiOS - [Gaming]• Optimization • Enable Game Mode
; ID: Gaming_EnableGameMode
; DESC: Enables Windows Game Mode.
; IMPACT: • Allows automatic activation of Game Mode for the user.
; IMPACT: • Forces Game Mode to be activated at the system level.
; IMPACT: • Game Mode prioritizes CPU/GPU resources for the current game, limits certain background tasks, and can improve FPS stability.
; RISK: • Impact varies depending on the game and configuration: some titles may show no benefit, or even a slight negative effect.
; RISK: • May reduce the priority of useful background tasks during gameplay (streaming, encoding, saving).
; RISK: • No risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: Gaming setting / automatic optimization: lets Windows intelligently manage priorities during games. Generally beneficial and safe.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\GameBar]
"AllowAutoGameMode"=dword:00000001

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\PolicyManager\default\ApplicationManagement\AllowGameMode]
"value"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Gaming]• Latency • Disable dynamic timer throttling (latency)
; ID: Gaming_DisableTimerThrottling
; DESC: Allows applications to force a finer global system timer resolution.
; IMPACT: • Allows apps (games, real-time audio, emulators, low-latency engines) to reduce the Windows timer resolution globally.
; IMPACT: • Can improve responsiveness, reduce latency, and smooth frametimes in certain real-time scenarios.
; IMPACT: • Effect depends on the applications actually capable of making these requests.
; RISK: • Increased power consumption (CPU wakes up more often), especially on laptops.
; RISK: • Potential impact on battery life and heat if an app continuously maintains a very low resolution.
; RISK: • No risk to system stability.
; NOTE: Latency/real-time setting: useful for gaming and professional audio. Best used on high-performance desktop PCs; Optional on laptops if battery life is a priority.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\Kernel]
"GlobalTimerResolutionRequests"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Gaming]• Optimization • GPU/CPU/Disk priority for games (MMCSS)
; ID: Gaming_MMCSS
; DESC: Increases GPU/CPU & Disk priorities to favor in•game resources.
; IMPACT: • Sets high priority for tasks classified as Games by MMCSS.
; IMPACT: • May improve graphics responsiveness on some engines.
; IMPACT: • Promote CPU allocation to game processes.
; IMPACT: • Can stabilize FPS if the CPU is heavily loaded.
; IMPACT: • Gives high I/O (disk) priority to game-related tasks.
; IMPACT: • Can reduce certain micro-stutters related to CPU/I/O contention.
; IMPACT: • Can improve fluidity, reduce latency and stabilize frametimes.
; RISK: • May penalize other background processes (stream, encoding, VM).
; RISK: • On weak CPUs, can unbalance the system planning.
; RISK: • Some values ​​are already close to the default on Windows 10/11 (sometimes minimal impact).
; RISK: • No risk of system stability.
; NOTE: • Gaming / MMCSS setting: useful on dedicated gaming configuration, especially without heavy multitasking.
; NOTE: • Avoid if you are streaming/recording at the same time (risk of starving other tasks).
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Multimedia\SystemProfile\Tasks\Games]
"GPU Priority"=dword:00000008
"Priority"=dword:00000006
"Scheduling Category"="High"
"SFIO Priority"="High"

; KORSiOS - [Gaming]• Latency • Disable Dynamic Window Mode (DWM) optimizations
; ID: Gaming_DisableDWM
; DESC: Disables fullscreen optimizations for windowed/borderless applications.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from applying DWM optimizations to windowed or borderless applications.
; IMPACT: • Forces a more traditional behavior, close to exclusive fullscreen.
; IMPACT: • May reduce some display bugs, latency, or performance inconsistencies (FPS, G-Sync/FreeSync, Alt-Tab).
; RISK: • Loss of some modern advantages (better HDR handling, smoother transitions, optimized capture).
; RISK: • Variable impact depending on the game and drivers; sometimes no gain.
; RISK: • No risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: Gaming compatibility/stability setting: useful for fixing issues in borderless mode or with certain graphics engines.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\Dwm]
"EnableWindowedOptimizations"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Gaming]• Security • HVCI / Memory Integrity
; ID: Gaming_HVCI
; DESC: Disables hypervisor-enforced code integrity protection (HVCI / Memory Integrity).
; IMPACT: • Disables HVCI (Hypervisor-Enforced Code Integrity), a component of Device Guard / VBS.
; IMPACT: • Removes security virtualization that checks drivers and code in memory.
; IMPACT: • Can improve CPU/GPU performance, reduce latency, and prevent driver incompatibilities (old or unsigned drivers).
; RISK: • Reduced security level: less protection against malicious drivers and certain kernel attacks.
; RISK: • Avoid on exposed or sensitive machines (professional, enterprise, uncontrolled workstations).
; RISK: • No direct risk to stability.
; NOTE: Performance/Driver Compatibility Tuning: Often used for gaming, overclocking, or specific drivers. Use only in a controlled environment where you are aware of the risks.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\DeviceGuard\Scenarios\HypervisorEnforcedCodeIntegrity]
"Enabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [GPU]• Stability • Disable MPO
; ID: Gaming_MPO
; DESC: Disables the Multi-Plane Overlay (MPO) of the Windows Graphics Engine (DWM).
; IMPACT: • Forces DWM to stop using MPO for graphics rendering.
; IMPACT: • May reduce flickering, black screens, micro-freezes, or compatibility issues (often related to GPU drivers).
; IMPACT: • Rendering uses a more conventional and stable path.
; RISK: • Slight loss of graphics optimization in some scenarios.
; RISK: • On perfectly stable systems with MPO enabled, the gain may be negligible.
; RISK: • No risk to security or critical stability.
; NOTE: Graphics stability setting: widely used to correct display bugs (especially with certain GPU drivers), recommended if visual problems are present.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\Dwm]
"OverlayTestMode"=dword:00000005

; KORSiOS - [GPU]• Performance • HAGS
; ID: Gaming_HAGS
; DESC: Forces hardware GPU scheduling (HAGS) to the enabled state.
; IMPACT: • Enables Hardware Accelerated GPU Scheduling.
; IMPACT: • Offloads some GPU scheduling from the CPU to the GPU itself.
; IMPACT: • Can reduce latency, improve smoothness, and stabilize performance in some games and graphics applications.
; IMPACT: • Effect depends on the GPU driver and hardware (recent NVIDIA/AMD drivers).
; RISK: • Variable compatibility: on some configurations/drivers, may cause micro-stutters, graphical glitches, or instability.
; RISK: • No hardware risk, setting easily reversible.
; RISK: • May have no noticeable effect depending on usage.
; NOTE: GPU performance setting: to be tested on a case by case basis. Often beneficial on recent gaming-oriented configurations, but disable it if problems arise.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\GraphicsDrivers]
"HwSchMode"=dword:00000002

; KORSiOS - [GPU]• Stability • TDR
; ID: Gaming_TDR
; DESC: Increases TDR delays to prevent GPU timeouts and unexpected graphics driver resets.
; IMPACT: • Gives the GPU 10 seconds to respond before a reset is triggered.
; IMPACT: • Gives the driver (DDI) an additional 20 seconds to complete its operations.
; IMPACT: • Reduces driver crashes, black screens, and TDR errors under heavy loads (rendering, encoding, gaming, GPU computing).
; RISK: • Longer freeze in case of a true GPU crash (the system waits longer to recover).
; RISK: • May mask an actual hardware or driver problem.
; RISK: • Avoid on undiagnosed unstable systems.
; NOTE: GPU stability setting / heavy workloads: useful for preventing unexpected resets under heavy load.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\GraphicsDrivers]
"TdrDelay"=dword:0000000a
"TdrDdiDelay"=dword:00000014

; KORSiOS - [GPU]• Latency • Force low GPU latency for the Desktop Window Manager
; ID: GPU_GPULatency
; DESC: Forces a minimum latency tolerance for the DWM graphics engine.
; IMPACT: • Tells DWM not to tolerate additional latency in the graphics composition.
; IMPACT: • Can promote maximum display responsiveness (input → rendering → display).
; IMPACT: • Useful in gaming, real-time, or low perceived latency scenarios.
; RISK: • Variable stability depending on GPU/drivers: some systems may experience micro-stuttering or tearing if the pipeline is too strict.
; RISK: • Sometimes no gain on already well optimized configurations.
; RISK: • No risk of security or corruption.
; NOTE: Advanced graphics latency setting: consider it a fine tuning adjustment to reduce display latency. To be tested and validated empirically (games, frametimes).
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\Dwm]
"LatencyTolerance"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [GPU]• Performance • PCIe ASPM Power Management
; ID: GPU_PCIeASPM
; DESC: Disables PCIe ASPM (Active State Power Management).
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from using ASPM for PCIe links.
; IMPACT: • Keeps PCIe devices (GPU, NVMe, controllers) in high performance states.
; IMPACT: • Can reduce latency and prevent some stability issues (freezes, link losses).
; IMPACT: • Increases power consumption.
; RISK: • Increased power consumption and heat, especially on laptops.
; RISK: • Reduced battery life.
; RISK: • No direct risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: • PCIe stability/performance setting: useful for gaming and high-performance desktop systems, to be avoided on laptops if battery life is a priority.
; NOTE: • BIOS add-on recommended
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Power]
"ASPMDisabled"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Context Menu]• Classic • Enable Classic Context Menu
; ID: ContextMenu_ClassicContextMenu
; DESC: Restores the classic Windows 10 context menu in File Explorer.
; IMPACT: • Forces Windows 11 to use the old right-click menu instead of the modern, simplified one.
; IMPACT: • Directly displays all options (7-Zip, Notepad++, drivers, third-party tools, etc.) without going through "Show more options".
; RISK: • No risk to stability.
; NOTE: Saves time by making the full right-click menu immediately accessible.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Classes\CLSID]

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Classes\CLSID\{86ca1aa0-34aa-4e8b-a509-50c905bae2a2}]

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Classes\CLSID\{86ca1aa0-34aa-4e8b-a509-50c905bae2a2}\InprocServer32]
@=""

; KORSiOS - [Context Menu] • Shortcuts • Adding Control Panel Access
; ID: ContextMenu_ControlPanel
; DESC: Adds a "Control Panel" shortcut to the Desktop right-click menu.
; IMPACT: • Creates a new entry in the Desktop context menu.
; IMPACT: • Displays the "Control Panel" option with its icon.
; IMPACT: • The entry is positioned at the bottom of the menu.
; RISK: • No technical or stability risks.
; NOTE: Ergonomic design / quick access: ideal for instantly finding the Control Panel from the Desktop, without using search or modern settings.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\DesktopBackground\Shell\Panneau de configuration]
"Icon"="control.exe"
"MUIVerb"="Panneau de configuration"
"Position"="Bottom"

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\DesktopBackground\Shell\Panneau de configuration\command]
@="control.exe"

; KORSiOS - [Context Menu] • Shortcuts • Added access to CMD Admin
; ID: ContextMenu_CMD
; DESC: Adds an “Open Terminal as Admin” option to the right-click menu for folders, the root directory, and drives.
; IMPACT: • Adds a right-click → administrator elevation entry.
; IMPACT: • Opens cmd.exe as administrator, directly in the selected path.
; IMPACT: • Significantly improves productivity for system tasks and scripts.
; RISK: • No technical or stability risks.
; NOTE: Power-user/administration setting: allows instant opening of an administrator terminal in the correct folder, very useful for troubleshooting or scripting.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\shell\runas]
@="Ouvrir le Terminal en mode Admin"
"HasLUAShield"=""

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\shell\runas\command]
@="cmd.exe /s /k pushd \"%V\""

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\Background\shell\runas]
@="Ouvrir le Terminal en mode Admin"
"HasLUAShield"=""

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\Background\shell\runas\command]
@="cmd.exe /s /k pushd \"%V\""

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Drive\shell\runas]
@="Ouvrir le Terminal en mode Admin"
"HasLUAShield"=""

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Drive\shell\runas\command]
@="cmd.exe /s /k pushd \"%V\""

; KORSiOS - [Context Menu]• Shortcuts • Added Registry Editor Access
; ID: ContextMenu_Registry
; DESC: Adds a "Registry Editor" shortcut to the Desktop right-click menu.
; IMPACT: • Adds a new entry to the Desktop background context menu.
; IMPACT: • Launches Regedit with its official icon in a new instance.
; IMPACT: • Significantly improves productivity for system tasks and scripts.
; RISK: • No technical or stability risks.
; NOTE: Administration/power-user setting: useful for quickly opening the Registry from the Desktop, use with caution due to the sensitivity of system settings.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\DesktopBackground\Shell\OpenRegedit]
"MUIVerb"="Editeur du Registre"
"Icon"="regedit.exe,0"

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\DesktopBackground\Shell\OpenRegedit\Command]
@="regedit -m"

; KORSiOS - [Context Menu]• Shortcuts • Added Firewall Access
; ID: ContextMenu_Firewall
; DESC: Adds a "Windows Firewall" menu to right-click on .exe files, allowing you to instantly block or allow a program through the firewall.
; IMPACT: • Creates a context menu entry on all executables (.exe).
; IMPACT: • Offers two actions: "Block" & "Allow"
; IMPACT: • Actions are executed via PowerShell in administrator mode.
; IMPACT: • Rules are created dynamically with the program name.
; RISK: • Rule management: if multiple rules have similar names or if the path changes, deletion may not target the expected rule.
; RISK: • No security risk
; NOTE: Very convenient/power-user setting: allows for precise and quick control of application network access, ideal for testing, securing, or limiting traffic without using the full Windows Firewall interface.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\exefile\shell\WindowsFirewall]
@=""
"MUIVerb"="Pare-Feu Windows"
"icon"="%SystemRoot%\\system32\\FirewallControlPanel.dll,0"
"subcommands"=""

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\exefile\shell\WindowsFirewall\Shell]
@=""

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\exefile\shell\WindowsFirewall\Shell\block]
@=""
"MUIVerb"="Bloquer"
"icon"="%SystemRoot%\\system32\\imageres.dll,100"

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\exefile\shell\WindowsFirewall\Shell\block\command]
@="\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe\" -Executionpolicy ByPass -WindowStyle Hidden -NoLogo -Command \"start powershell -Verb runas -ArgumentList \\\"-NoLogo -WindowStyle Hidden -command `\\\"New-NetFirewallRule -DisplayName ([System.IO.Path]::GetFilenameWithoutExtension('%1')) -Name '%1' -Enabled True -Direction Outbound -Action Block -Program '%1'`\\\"\\\"\""

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\exefile\shell\WindowsFirewall\Shell\Remove]
@=""
"MUIVerb"="Autoriser"
"icon"="%SystemRoot%\\system32\\imageres.dll,101"

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\exefile\shell\WindowsFirewall\Shell\Remove\command]
@="\"C:\\Windows\\System32\\WindowsPowerShell\\v1.0\\powershell.exe\" -Executionpolicy ByPass -WindowStyle Hidden -NoLogo -Command \"start powershell -Verb runas -ArgumentList \\\"-NoLogo -WindowStyle Hidden -command `\\\"Remove-NetFirewallRule -Name '%1'`\\\"\\\"\""

; KORSiOS - [Context Menu]• Shortcuts • Added "Take Control" Function
; ID: ContextMenu_Control
; DESC: Adds the "Take Control" option to right-clicking files and folders, allowing you to take ownership and obtain full rights.
; IMPACT: • Adds an entry to the context menu for folders and files.
; IMPACT: • Changes the owner of the selected object.
; IMPACT: • Grants full rights to the current user.
; IMPACT: • For folders, the action is recursive (including files and subfolders).
; IMPACT: • Allows modification/deletion of normally protected files (system, Program Files, etc.).
; RISK: • High risk if misused (modifying system files can break Windows).
; RISK: • Can create inconsistent permissions if applied extensively.
; NOTE: Advanced administration/troubleshooting settings: extremely useful for unlocking locked files, but use with caution, especially on critical system components.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\*\shell\Takeowner]
@="Prendre le controle"
"HasLUAShield"=""
"NoWorkingDirectory"=""
"Position"="middle"

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\*\shell\Takeowner\command]
@="powershell -windowstyle hidden -command \"Start-Process cmd -ArgumentList '/c takeown /f \\\"%1\\\" && icacls \\\"%1\\\" /grant *S-1-3-4:F /c /l' -Verb runAs\""
"IsolatedCommand"="powershell -windowstyle hidden -command \"Start-Process cmd -ArgumentList '/c takeown /f \\\"%1\\\" && icacls \\\"%1\\\" /grant *S-1-3-4:F /c /l' -Verb runAs\""

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\shell\Takeowner]
@="Prendre le controle"
"HasLUAShield"=""
"NoWorkingDirectory"=""
"Position"="middle"

[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\shell\Takeowner\command]
@="powershell -windowstyle hidden -command \"Start-Process cmd -ArgumentList '/c takeown /f \\\"%1\\\" /r /d o && icacls \\\"%1\\\" /grant *S-1-3-4:F /c /l /q' -Verb runAs\""
"IsolatedCommand"="powershell -windowstyle hidden -command \"Start-Process cmd -ArgumentList '/c takeown /f \\\"%1\\\" /r /d o && icacls \\\"%1\\\" /grant *S-1-3-4:F /t /c /l /q' -Verb runAs\""

; KORSiOS - [Start Menu] Disable Recommendations/Suggestions
; ID: StartMenu_DisableSuggestions
; DESC: Disables recommendations in the Windows Start Menu.
; IMPACT: • Removes suggested apps, files, or content from the Start Menu Recommendations section.
; IMPACT: • The Start Menu becomes cleaner and more static, focused on pinned apps.
; RISK: • Loss of useful suggestions (recent files, recently used apps).
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Minimalist UX/anti-suggestion setting: ideal for a clean and distraction-free Start Menu.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"Start_IrisRecommendations"=dword:00000000

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\ContentDeliveryManager]
"SystemPaneSuggestionsEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Start Menu] Disable tracking of recently used apps
; ID: StartMenu_DisableTrackingApps
; DESC: Disables the list of most used apps.
; IMPACT: • Reduces suggestions and recommendations in Start.
; IMPACT: • Slightly improves privacy (less local tracking).
; RISK: • You lose the automatic display of "frequently used apps".
; RISK: • No system risk.
; NOTE: Start Menu clean + privacy setting: perfect for a minimal Start Menu.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"Start_TrackProgs"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Start Menu] Disable Recent Document Tracking
; ID: StartMenu_DisableTrackingDoc
; DESC: Disables recent document history in Windows.
; IMPACT: Prevents Windows from displaying recently opened files in:
; IMPACT: - Start Menu
; IMPACT: - Quick Access (Explorer)
; IMPACT: - Recent Lists (Jump Lists)
; IMPACT: • Reduces suggestions based on your activity.
; RISK: • You lose quick access to recent documents (less convenient).
; RISK: • No risk to stability or performance.
; NOTE: Privacy setting + clean interface: ideal for removing "recent" items everywhere and keeping Windows more discreet.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\Advanced]
"Start_TrackDocs"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Metadata] Block device metadata download from the internet
; ID: Metadata_DisableMetadata
; DESC: Prevents Windows from downloading device metadata from the internet.
; IMPACT: • Blocks online retrieval of device icons, names, descriptions, and manufacturer information.
; IMPACT: • Windows uses only locally stored information.
; IMPACT: • Reduces automatic network access when new hardware is connected.
; IMPACT: • Applied via both policy and system key for maximum consistency.
; RISK: • More generic display of devices (standard icons, less detailed names).
; RISK: • No impact on the actual operation of drivers or devices.
; NOTE: Network privacy/cleanliness setting: avoids unnecessary external requests while maintaining normal hardware operation.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Device Metadata]
"PreventDeviceMetadataFromNetwork"=dword:00000001

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Device Metadata]
"PreventDeviceMetadataFromNetwork"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Notepad++] Replace Windows Notepad with Notepad++
; ID: Notepad_ReplaceNotepad
; DESCRIPTION: Replaces Notepad with Notepad++ and sets Notepad++ as the default editor for most text files and scripts.
; IMPACT: • Global Notepad redirection: opening notepad.exe launches Notepad++.
; IMPACT: • File association.
; IMPACT: • Creating new text files: "New > Text Document" creates a correctly associated empty file.
; IMPACT: • Script editing.
; IMPACT: • Allows editing/deleting normally protected files (system, Program Files, etc.).
; RISK: • Dependence on Notepad++: if uninstalled/moved, some opening/editing operations will fail.
; RISK: • In locked-down/corporate environments, may violate standard policies.
; NOTE: Productivity/Power User Setting: Notepad++ becomes the system's universal editor. Very practical and consistent, provided that Notepad++ is always installed on the machine.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Image File Execution Options\notepad.exe]
"Debugger"="\"C:\\Program Files\\Notepad++\\notepad++.exe\""

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\.txt]
@="KORSiOS.txtfile"
"Content Type"="text/plain"
"PerceivedType"="text"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\KORSiOS.txtfile]
@="Text Document (Notepad++)"
"FriendlyTypeName"="Document texte Notepad++"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\.txt\ShellNew]
"NullFile"=""

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\KORSiOS.txtfile\shell\open\command]
@="\"C:\\Program Files\\Notepad++\\notepad++.exe\" \"%1\""

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\.log]
@="KORSiOS.txtfile"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\.ini]
@="KORSiOS.txtfile"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\.cfg]
@="KORSiOS.txtfile"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\.conf]
@="KORSiOS.txtfile"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\.csv]
@="KORSiOS.txtfile"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\.xml]
@="KORSiOS.txtfile"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\.json]
@="KORSiOS.txtfile"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\.yaml]
@="KORSiOS.txtfile"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\.yml]
@="KORSiOS.txtfile"

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\regfile\shell\edit\command]
@="\"C:\\Program Files\\Notepad++\\notepad++.exe\" \"%1\""

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\batfile\shell\edit\command]
@="\"C:\\Program Files\\Notepad++\\notepad++.exe\" \"%1\""

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\cmdfile\shell\edit\command]
@="\"C:\\Program Files\\Notepad++\\notepad++.exe\" \"%1\""

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\VBSFile\Shell\Edit\Command]
@="\"C:\\Program Files\\Notepad++\\notepad++.exe\" \"%1\""

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Classes\Microsoft.PowerShellScript.1\Shell\Edit\Command]
@="\"C:\\Program Files\\Notepad++\\notepad++.exe\" \"%1\""

; KORSiOS - [Notifications]• Advertising • Disable “Sync Provider Notifications” in Explorer
; ID: Notifications_DisableSyncProvider
