"NoControlPanel"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Settings]Hide Home Page in Settings
; ID: Settings_HomePage
; DESC: Hides the Windows Settings app home page
; IMPACT: • The Settings app remains accessible, but the "Home" page is no longer displayed.
; IMPACT: • Reduces unnecessary visual elements and simplifies the interface.
; RISK: • No impact on internal functionality or system stability.
; RISK: • Easily reversible.
; NOTE: Cosmetic/UX setting: It cleans up the Settings interface without blocking access to advanced options.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer]
"SettingsPageVisibility"="hide:home"

; KORSiOS - [Settings]Hide Windows Insider in Settings
; ID: Settings_Insider
; DESC: Hide the “Windows Insider Program” section in Windows Update settings.
; IMPACT: • Prevents quick access to Insider build signup via the UI.
; IMPACT: • Removes the display of the Insider page in Settings.
; RISK: • May make Insider management less accessible if the machine is already enrolled.
; RISK: • Does not completely prevent Insider activation via other methods (policy/script).
; NOTE: Purely UI setting: useful for locking a machine in stable mode (no preview builds).
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\WindowsSelfHost\UI\Visibility]
"HideInsiderPage"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Performance]• Memory • Disable System Cache Extended
; ID: Performance_DisableSystemCache
; DESC: Disables the extended system cache to prioritize application memory.
; IMPACT: • Prioritizes RAM for applications over the system cache.
; IMPACT: • Reserves RAM primarily for active programs.
; IMPACT: • Optimal behavior for a desktop PC / gaming / everyday use.
; IMPACT: • Improves memory stability with certain drivers (especially GPUs).
; RISK: • Slight theoretical performance loss on file server workloads (very specific case).
; RISK: • No risk or negative impact.
; NOTE: • Optimal desktop memory setting: this is the recommended value for a high-performance PC.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\Memory Management]
"LargeSystemCache"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Performance]• Memory • Disable Memory Compression
; ID: Performance_MemoryCompression
; DESC: Disables Windows memory compression.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from compressing RAM when it is under pressure.
; IMPACT: • Reduces CPU usage related to memory compression/decompression.
; IMPACT: • Can make memory usage more predictable, especially on machines with a lot of RAM.
; RISK: • Higher RAM consumption: Windows will switch to the page file sooner.
; RISK: • On machines with little RAM, this can degrade performance.
; RISK: • No direct risk to stability.
; NOTE: • CPU performance adjustment / memory control: relevant on PCs with ample RAM (gaming, workstation), to be avoided on modest configurations.
; NOTE: • Real impact mainly on heavily loaded CPUs.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\Memory Management]
"DisableCompression"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Performance]• Memory • Disable virtual memory for certain parts of the kernel
; ID: Performance_DisableKernelVirtualMemory
; DESC: Prevents the Windows kernel from virtualizing certain parts of the kernel.
; IMPACT: • Forces the kernel and drivers to remain in RAM.
; IMPACT: • Reduces access to the page file for system code.
; IMPACT: • Can improve responsiveness and reduce some micro-latencies.
; IMPACT: • Relevant on machines with a lot of RAM.
; RISK: • Higher RAM consumption.
; RISK: • Not recommended on machines with little memory.
; RISK: • No risk of stability if RAM is sufficient (16GB+).
; NOTE: • Low latency setting / kernel in RAM: classic tweak for 16–32+ GB machines.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\Memory Management]
"DisablePagingExecutive"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Performance]• Power • Disable Power Throttling
; ID: Performance_DisablePowerThrottling
; DESC: Disables Windows Power Throttling.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from automatically throttling background application performance.
; IMPACT: • Keeps processes running at a consistent performance level, even when not in the foreground.
; IMPACT: • May improve responsiveness, performance stability, and reduce some micro-lags, especially during multitasking or gaming.
; RISK: • Increased power consumption, especially on laptops.
; RISK: • Potentially slightly increased heat depending on the load.
; RISK: • No risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: • Raw performance/anti-throttling setting: recommended for desktop PCs or performance-oriented configurations.
; NOTE: • Actual impact mainly on heavily loaded CPUs.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Power\PowerThrottling]
"PowerThrottlingOff"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Performance]• Optimization • Disable Fault Tolerant Heap (FTH)
; ID: Performance_FTH
; DESC: Disables Windows' Fault Tolerant Heap (FTH).
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from automatically enabling memory compatibility mode for unstable applications.
; IMPACT: • FTH is a mechanism that intentionally slows down certain apps to prevent crashes.
; IMPACT: • Disabling it removes this "protection" layer, which can improve the performance of some software.
; IMPACT: • Reduces automatic compatibility interventions.
; RISK: • Truly unstable applications may crash instead of being slowed down.
; RISK: • Only useful if you prioritize performance and manual control.
; RISK: • No risk to Windows itself.
; NOTE: Forced anti-compatibility/performance setting: intended for advanced users who want raw behavior without automatic fixes. 
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\Software\Microsoft\FTH]
"Enabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Performance]• Optimization • Disable background apps
; ID: Performance_DisableBackgroundApps
; DESC: Disables background app execution.
; IMPACT: • Blocks UWP/Microsoft Store apps from running in the background.
; IMPACT: • Reduces CPU activity, memory consumption, and hidden network access.
; IMPACT: • Improves battery life (laptops) and performance stability.
; RISK: • Some apps may no longer update in the background or send notifications (email, weather, messaging).
; RISK: • No impact on system stability or security.
; NOTE: • Anti-ghost apps setting / resource optimization: very effective at limiting unnecessary processes.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\BackgroundAccessApplications]
"GlobalUserDisabled"=dword:00000001
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\AppPrivacy]
"LetAppsRunInBackground"=dword:00000002

; KORSiOS - [Performance]• Indexing • Adapt indexing to Power supply modes
; ID: Performance_Indexing
; DESC: Configure Windows Search to respect power modes (battery / power saving).
; IMPACT: • Forces indexing to adapt to the active feeding mode.
; IMPACT: • Reduces or suspends intensive indexing in battery mode.
; IMPACT: • Reduces disk/CPU activity when the PC is in power saving mode.
; IMPACT: • Does not affect the overall functioning of the research (only its aggressiveness).
; RISK: • Indexing may be slower in battery mode.
; RISK: • New files may appear in the search results with a slight delay.
; NOTE: • Intelligent performance setting: recommended on laptops to optimize battery life.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\Software\Microsoft\Windows Search\Gather\Windows\SystemIndex]
"RespectPowerModes"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Peripherals / Keyboard / Mouse]• Mouse • Disable Windows Mouse Acceleration (Improved Accuracy)
; ID: Peripherals_DisableMouseAcceleration
; DESC: Disables Windows mouse acceleration.
; IMPACT: • Turns off software mouse acceleration.
; IMPACT: • Removes acceleration trigger thresholds.
; IMPACT: • Cursor movement becomes linear and predictable: the distance traveled depends solely on physical movement.
; RISK: • Different feel for users accustomed to Windows acceleration.
; RISK: • May require adjusting mouse DPI sensitivity.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or security.
; NOTE: Precision/gaming setting: essential for consistent and repeatable aiming, highly valued in FPS games and environments requiring constant precision.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\Mouse]
"MouseSpeed"="0"
"MouseThreshold1"="0"
"MouseThreshold2"="0"

; KORSiOS - [Peripherals / Keyboard / Mouse]• Mouse • Disable Mouse Idle Timer
; ID: Peripherals_DisableMouseIdleTimer
; DESC: Disables mouse inactivity detection.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from considering the mouse inactive after a certain period of time.
; IMPACT: • Prevents certain automatic behaviors related to inactivity (reduced polling, micro-pauses).
; IMPACT: • May improve consistent mouse responsiveness, especially in games.
; RISK: • Slightly higher power consumption (negligible) because the "idle" state is never reached.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or security.
; NOTE: Input/Consistency setting: ensures consistently active and predictable mouse behavior, appreciated in gaming and precise use.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\Mouse]
"MouseIdleThreshold"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Peripherals / Keyboard / Mouse]• Keyboard • Optimize Key Repeat
; ID: Peripherals_KeyRepeat
; DESC: Increases keyboard responsiveness by reducing latency and maximizing repeat rate.
; IMPACT: • Faster, more responsive typing, useful for intensive typing and some games.
; RISK: • Unintentional key repeats may occur if a key is held down for too long.
; RISK: • May require an adjustment period for sensitive users.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or security.
; NOTE: Precision/Gaming setting: Makes the keyboard more responsive and pleasant for fast typing or data entry.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\Keyboard]
"KeyboardDelay"="0"
"KeyboardSpeed"="31"

; KORSiOS - [Peripherals / Keyboard / Mouse]• Keyboard • Disable Sticky Keys (Remote Keys / Filters)
; ID: Peripherals_StickyKeys
; DESC: Disables keyboard accessibility features (Stick Keys, Filter Keys, Toggle Keys).
; IMPACT: • Disables Sticky Keys (prevents activation via repeated Shift key presses).
; IMPACT: • Disables Filter Keys (no delay or filtering of keystrokes).
; IMPACT: • Disables Toggle Keys (no sounds when activating Caps Lock, Num Lock, etc.).
; IMPACT: • Prevents accessibility pop-ups and unintentional interruptions during gameplay or rapid typing.
; RISK: • Accessibility features unavailable for users who need them.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Gaming/Keyboard Comfort setting: prevents accidental activation of accessibility options, highly recommended for gaming and intensive typing.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\Accessibility\StickyKeys]
"Flags"="506"

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\Accessibility\Keyboard Response]
"Flags"="122"

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\Accessibility\ToggleKeys]
"Flags"="58"

; KORSiOS - [Peripherals / Keyboard / Mouse]• USB • Disable HID Device Sleep Mode
; ID: Peripherals_DisableHIDSpleepMode
; DESC: Disables USB selective sleep mode for HID devices (keyboard, mouse, controllers).
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from automatically putting USB-connected HID devices to sleep.
; IMPACT: • Reduces temporary disconnections, latency, or loss of response (mouse/keyboard/controllers/steering wheel going to sleep).
; IMPACT: • Improves the responsiveness and stability of input devices, especially during gaming or intensive use.
; RISK: • Slightly higher power consumption, especially on laptops.
; RISK: • No impact on system stability or security.
; NOTE: Stability/Input setting: very useful for avoiding USB issues with mice and keyboards, recommended for desktop PCs or performance-oriented configurations.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\HidUsb\Parameters]
"SelectiveSuspendEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Peripherals / Keyboard / Mouse]• USB • Disable USB Hub Sleep Mode
; ID: Peripherals_DisableUSBHubSleepMode
; DESC: Disables idle power management for USB 3.x controllers.
; IMPACT: • Prevents the USBHUB3 controller from entering a low-power state when inactive.
; IMPACT: • Reduces USB disconnections, wake-up delays, and micro-interruptions (mouse, keyboard, DAC, gaming peripherals).
; IMPACT: • Improves the stability and responsiveness of USB devices, especially under load or in light sleep mode.
; RISK: • Slightly higher power consumption, especially on laptops.
; RISK: • No impact on system stability or security.
; NOTE: USB stability/performance setting: very useful for avoiding intermittent USB issues, recommended for desktop PCs or performance-oriented configurations.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\USBHUB3\Parameters]
"DisableIdlePowerManagement"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Power]• Wake-up • Prevent PC Wake-up by Automatic Maintenance
; ID: Power_WakeupMaintenance
; DESC: Prevents automatic maintenance from waking the PC.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from waking the PC from sleep to perform scheduled maintenance.
; IMPACT: • Maintenance will only run when the PC is already powered on.
; IMPACT: • Reduces unexpected nighttime wake-ups.
; IMPACT: • Prevents unnecessary power consumption in sleep mode.
; RISK: • Some maintenance tasks may be delayed if the PC is frequently turned off.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or security.
; NOTE: Anti•ghost wake-up setting: ideal for preventing the PC from turning itself back on.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Schedule\Maintenance]
"WakeUp"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Power]• Sleep • Disable Hibernation
; ID: Power_Hibernation
; DESC: Completely disables Windows hibernation.
; IMPACT: • Prevents the use of hibernation and its dependent functions (Fast Startup).
; IMPACT: • Removes the use of the hiberfil.sys file, freeing up several GB of disk space.
; IMPACT: • The system will only use regular shutdown and sleep.
; RISK: • Loss of fast startup and full session recovery after shutdown.
; RISK: • On laptops, may reduce battery life in hibernation mode.
; RISK: • No risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: System performance/cleanup setting: useful on desktop PCs to save disk space and avoid hybrid states, less recommended on laptops where hibernation can be useful.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Power]
"HibernateEnabled"=dword:00000000
"HibernateEnabledDefault"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Power]• Sleep • Disable Fast Startup / Hybrid Boot
; ID: Power_FastStartUp
; DESC: Disables Windows Fast Startup / Hybrid Boot.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from using hibernation-based hybrid boot.
; IMPACT: • Forces a true full shutdown on every power off.
; IMPACT: • Improves the stability of drivers, USB/GPU/network devices after reboot.
; IMPACT: • Avoids some bugs related to hybrid states (dual boot, updates, overclocking, drivers).
; IMPACT: • Boot time may be slightly longer.
; RISK: • Slightly longer boot time.
; RISK: • No impact on security or stability.
; NOTE: Boot stability setting: recommended on optimized, overclocked, or multi-OS machines. Eliminates unusual hybrid states.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\Power]
"HiberbootEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Windows Search]• Web • Disable web/Bing search in the Start menu
; ID: Search_DisableBingStart
; DESC: Disables online suggestions in the Windows search bar.
; IMPACT: • Prevents the display of web results, trends, and Bing suggestions in search.
; IMPACT: • Search remains local (applications, files, settings).
; IMPACT: • Reduces network queries and promotional content.
; RISK: • Loss of integrated web search from the search bar.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Privacy/Clean Search setting: Keeps searches fast and local without web clutter.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Explorer]
"DisableSearchBoxSuggestions"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Windows Search]• Web • Disable Search Highlights
; ID: Search_DisableHighlights
; DESC: Disables the dynamic search bar (Smart Search Box).
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from displaying an "adaptive" search (content, suggestions, highlights).
; IMPACT: • Makes the search area simpler/more neutral.
; IMPACT: • Reduces promotional/trending elements related to search.
; RISK: • No risk.
; RISK: • May remove some "modern" search features (topics, visual suggestions).
; NOTE: Clean UI setting + light privacy: good tweak to limit "assisted" search and maintain a clean interface.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Windows Search]
"EnableDynamicContentInWSB"=dword:00000000
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\SearchSettings]
"IsDynamicSearchBoxEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Windows Search] • Indexing • Disable Windows Search
; ID: Search_DisableWS
; DESC: Completely disables Windows Search service
; IMPACT: • Stops file indexing.
; IMPACT: • Reduces background disk activity.
; IMPACT: • Reduces CPU usage related to indexing.
; IMPACT: • Can improve responsiveness on old PCs or mechanical drives.
; RISK: • Windows search becomes much slower (raw search without index).
; RISK: • Start Menu may become slow during searches.
; RISK: • Some index-dependent UWP apps may malfunction.
; NOTE: • Performance adjustment: useful especially on very limited HDDs or PCs.
; NOTE: • On modern SSD, the gain is often low, and the loss of comfort is significant.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\WSearch]
"Start"=dword:00000004

; KORSiOS - [Windows Search]• Web • Disable Cloud Search
; ID: Search_DisableCloudSearch
; DESC: Disables cloud search in Windows Search.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows Search from displaying results from the cloud (e.g., OneDrive / connected content).
; IMPACT: • Makes searching more local and simpler.
; IMPACT: • Reduces network traffic related to search.
; RISK: • No risk to stability.
; RISK: • OneDrive files or cloud content may be less well indexed/less visible via Windows Search.
; NOTE: Privacy setting + local search: perfectly complements the "Disable Bing / Web in Windows Search" tweak.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Windows Search]
"AllowCloudSearch"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Windows Search]• Web • Disable Bing/Web in Windows Search
; ID: Search_DisableBingSearch
; DESC: Disables web search in Windows Search (Start menu/search bar).
; IMPACT: • Cuts off Bing/Web integration in Windows Search.
; IMPACT: • Prevents the use of the internet for search.
; IMPACT: • Search becomes local only (apps, files, settings).
; RISK: • Loss of web results (Bing, suggestions, news).
; RISK: • On some versions of Windows 11, Microsoft may partially work around this via updates (variable effect).
; RISK: • No risk to stability.
; NOTE: Privacy + debloat setting: makes search cleaner, faster, and less "connected".
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Windows Search]
"DisableWebSearch"=dword:00000001
"ConnectedSearchUseWeb"=dword:00000000
"ConnectedSearchUseWebOverMeteredConnections"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Windows Search]• History • Disable search history
; ID: Search_DisableSearchHistory
; DESC: Disables search history on the device.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from remembering searches performed in the Start menu / Windows Search.
; IMPACT: • Reduces suggestions based on your previous searches.
; IMPACT: • Slightly improves privacy.
; RISK: • Loss of the convenience of recent searches (autocomplete / history).
; RISK: • No impact on performance or stability.
; NOTE: Simple privacy setting: a good complement to tweaks that make search 100% local and minimalist.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\SearchSettings]
"IsDeviceSearchHistoryEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Network]• Latency • Disable Network Throttling
; ID: Network_DisableNetworkThrottling
; DESC: Disables the software throttling of network traffic imposed by Windows for multimedia applications.
; IMPACT: • Removes the network throttling applied by the multimedia scheduler (MMCSS).
; IMPACT: • Allows real-time applications (online games, streaming, audio/video, VoIP) to fully utilize available bandwidth.
; RISK: On slow or shared networks, this may cause latency spikes for secondary tasks.
; NOTE: Very common setting in gaming/streaming profiles: Windows no longer throttles the network for multimedia tasks and prioritizes active applications.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Multimedia\SystemProfile]
"NetworkThrottlingIndex"=dword:ffffffff

; KORSiOS - [Network]• Control • Disable OEM imposed automatic WiFi connection
; ID: Network_DisableAutoWiFi
; DESC: Disables OEM imposed automatic WiFi connection.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from using OEM rules to automatically connect to WiFi networks.
; IMPACT: • Windows no longer automatically connects to manufacturer preconfigured networks.
; IMPACT: • The user retains full control over WiFi connections.
; RISK: • Manual connection required on some previously auto-connected networks.
; RISK: • No impact on network stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Network control/privacy setting: Prevents unwanted automatic WiFi connections defined by the OEM.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\WcmSvc\wifinetworkmanager\config]
"AutoConnectAllowedOEM"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Network]• Control • Disable paid Wi-Fi network management
; ID: Network_PaidWiFi
; DESC: Disables the detection/management feature for paid Wi-Fi networks (Hotspot 2.0 / Paid WiFi).
; IMPACT: • Windows will no longer automatically offer connections to compatible commercial hotspots.
; IMPACT: • Does not affect regular Wi-Fi connection (standard SSID).
; RISK: • It is not possible to automatically use certain integrated paid public hotspots.
; RISK: • May require manual login via browser if using a captive hotspot.
; NOTE: “Clean network” setting: useful if you never use paid Wi-Fi/operator hotspot.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\WcmSvc\wifinetworkmanager\features]
"PaidWifi"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Network]• Control • Disable Wi-Fi Sense (open networks suggested)
; ID: Network_SenseWiFi
; DESC: Disables the Wi-Fi Sense feature that offered/allowed automatic connection to suggested open networks.
; IMPACT: • Reduces unsolicited automatic Wi-Fi connections.
; IMPACT: • Limits exposure to potentially unsecured public networks.
; RISK: • Less practical when travelling if you want to have an automatic connection to open hotspots.
; NOTE:  Network setting “privacy / security”: recommended to avoid automatic connections to open networks.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\WcmSvc\wifinetworkmanager\features]
"WiFiSenseOpen"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Network]• Monitoring • Disable NDU (Network Data Usage Monitoring)
; ID: Network_DisableNDU
; DESC: Disables the Windows NDU (Network Data Usage Monitoring) service.
; IMPACT: • May reduce micro-latency (especially in online games).
; IMPACT: • Prevents network usage monitoring and recording by application.
; IMPACT: • May slightly reduce CPU/RAM usage and some disk writes related to network monitoring.
; IMPACT: • Network usage statistics in Settings may become incomplete or missing.
; RISK: • Loss of detailed network usage statistics by application.
; RISK: • No impact on connectivity, actual network performance, or security.
; RISK: • Some advanced network diagnostic features may be limited.
; NOTE: Low power/anti local telemetry setting: Turns off no essential network usage monitoring for a more discreet and lightweight system.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\Ndu]
"Start"=dword:00000004

; KORSiOS - [Network]• Latency • Disable Nagle to Reduce TCP Latency
; ID: Network_DisableNagle
; DESC: Reduces network latency by disabling certain TCP delays (Nagle/ACK batching).
; IMPACT: • Forces ACKs to be sent immediately instead of batching them.
; IMPACT: • Disables the Nagle algorithm (no waiting to batch packets).
; IMPACT: • Reduces latency in online games and real-time applications.
; IMPACT: • May improve network responsiveness on stable connections.
; IMPACT: • Applied per network interface (related to the card's GUID).
; RISK: • Increases the number of network packets sent.
; RISK: • May slightly increase network/CPU load on slow connections.
; RISK: • No risk to system stability.
; NOTE: Classic low latency gaming setting: widely used to optimize online games. Gains vary depending on ISP and game.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\Tcpip\Parameters\Interfaces\{NIC_GUID}]
"TcpAckFrequency"=dword:00000001
"TCPNoDelay"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [SSD / HDD]• NTFS • Disable NTFS “Last Access Time”
; ID: Drive_DisableNTFSLastAccess
; DESC: Disables updating the last access time of NTFS files.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from updating the Last Access timestamp each time a file is opened.
; IMPACT: • Reduces unnecessary disk writes and may slightly improve performance, especially on large volumes.
; IMPACT: • No impact on file access, modification, or creation.
; RISK: Very specific applications that may depend on the “last access” field (rare) will see this information frozen.
; RISK: • No impact on data stability, security, or integrity.
; NOTE: Performance/disk efficiency setting: classic and recommended on modern systems to limit unnecessary writes.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\FileSystem]
"NtfsDisableLastAccessUpdate"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [SSD / HDD]• SysMain • Disable SysMain (Superfetch) (perf/SSD option)
; ID: Drive_DisableSysMain
; DESC: Disables the SysMain service (formerly Superfetch).
; IMPACT: • Completely disables SysMain.
; IMPACT: • Prevents usage pattern analysis and application preloading into memory.
; IMPACT: • May reduce background disk and CPU activity.
; IMPACT: • Effect most noticeable on fast SSDs and already high-performance systems.
; RISK: • Slight increase in launch times for some applications on HDDs or less powerful machines.
; RISK: • On modern SSDs, the impact is generally negligible.
; RISK: • No risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: Low power consumption/controlled performance setting: often unnecessary on recent SSDs, disabling SysMain makes system behavior more predictable.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\SysMain]
"Start"=dword:00000004

; KORSiOS - [SSD / HDD]• Prefetch • Disable Application Prefetch
; ID: Drive_DisablePrefetch
; DESC: Disables the Windows Prefetcher.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from preloading application and system data into memory.
; IMPACT: • Reduces disk access and background activity related to prefetching.
; IMPACT: • Impact is most noticeable on fast SSDs where the benefit of prefetching is small.
; RISK: • Slightly longer launch times for some applications, especially on HDDs or less powerful machines.
; RISK: • On modern SSDs, the impact is generally negligible.
; RISK: • No risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: Memory management/control setting: often unnecessary on recent SSDs, disabling the Prefetcher makes system behavior more predictable.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\Memory Management\PrefetchParameters]
"EnablePrefetcher"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [SSD / HDD]• Prefetch • Reduce Prefetch
; ID: Drive_ReducePrefetchStart
; DESC: Enables Prefetch only for Windows startup.
; IMPACT: • Optimizes boot time by preloading system files.
; IMPACT: • Does not prefetch applications.
; IMPACT: • Reduces disk activity compared to full mode.
; IMPACT: • Good compromise between fast boot and a clean system.
; RISK: • Applications no longer benefit from prefetching → first launch may be slightly slower.
; RISK: • Virtually no impact on modern SSDs.
; RISK: • No risk to stability or security.
; NOTE: Intelligent SSD compromise setting: maintains optimized boot without unnecessary disk noise.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\Memory Management\PrefetchParameters]
"EnablePrefetcher"=dword:00000002

; KORSiOS - [SSD / HDD]• NTFS • Disable 8.3 Short Filenames
; ID: Drive_DisableShortFilenames
; DESC: Disables the creation of 8.3 short filenames on NTFS volumes.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from generating DOS 8.3 aliases for new files/folders.
; IMPACT: • Reduces file system overhead during file creation.
; IMPACT: • Slightly improves I/O performance, especially on volumes containing many small files.
; IMPACT: • Does not affect existing files.
; RISK: • Very old (DOS / legacy) software that may rely on 8.3 filenames may no longer function correctly.
; RISK: • No impact on modern software.
; RISK: • No risk to system stability.
; NOTE: NTFS performance/legacy cleanup tweak: a clean and recommended tweak on modern systems. Removes unnecessary legacy compatibility.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\FileSystem]
"NtfsDisable8dot3NameCreation"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [System]• Diagnostics • Disable Windows Error Reporting
; ID: System_DisableErrorReporting
; DESC: Completely disables Windows Error Reporting (WER).
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from collecting and sending error/crash reports to Microsoft.
; IMPACT: • Suppresses pop-ups prompting you to send a report after a crash.
; IMPACT: • Reduces background activity related to dump and diagnostic collection.
; RISK: • Less diagnostic information available in case of a crash.
; RISK: • Some applications that rely on WER for reporting may provide less detail.
; RISK: • No impact on system stability or security.
; NOTE: Privacy/Sobriety setting: disables error reporting while allowing the system to function normally.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Windows Error Reporting]
"Disabled"=dword:00000001

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\Windows Error Reporting]
"Disabled"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [System]• Notifications • Disable Action Center Panel + toast notifications
; ID: System_DisableActionCente
; DESC: Completely disables the Windows Action Center/Notifications.
; IMPACT: • Removes access to the Action Center/Notifications.
; IMPACT: • No system or application notifications are displayed.
; IMPACT: • Applied at both the system and user levels for complete and consistent blocking.
; RISK: • Loss of important information (security alerts, battery, network, updates).
; RISK: • May disrupt some notification dependent workflows.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or performance.
; NOTE: Anti-distraction/minimalism setting: ideal for a quiet and focused environment; use with caution on a well-managed system.
; RESTART: EXPLORER
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\Explorer]
"DisableNotificationCenter"=dword:00000001
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\PushNotifications]
"ToastEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [System]• Security • Disable Admin Approval Mode
; ID: System_DisableAdminApproval
; DESC: Disables User Account Control (UAC) mode for the built-in Administrator account.
; IMPACT: • Allows the built-in Administrator account to use a full administrator token permanently.
; IMPACT: • Suppresses UAC elevation requests for this specific account.
; IMPACT: • Other administrator accounts are not affected by this key.
; RISK: • Increased security risk : any application launched under this account immediately has full privileges.
; RISK: • An error, script, or malware would have maximum impact.
; NOTE: Advanced administration setting: useful for controlled environments, system scripts, or installation phases, but should only be used with caution.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\System]
"FilterAdministratorToken"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [System]• Shutdown • Time to Kill Apps > 3000
; ID: System_TimeToKillApps
; DESC: Reduces the wait time before services are forcibly shut down when Windows is shut down or restarted.
; IMPACT: • Sets the wait time to 3 seconds (3000 ms) before Windows forces services to stop.
; IMPACT: • Speeds up system shutdowns and restarts.
; IMPACT: • Limits the time allowed for services to shut down cleanly.
; RISK: • Low risk of data corruption or loss if a critical service does not have enough time to shut down properly.
; RISK: • May affect some resource intensive services (local databases, network services, VMs, indexing).
; RISK: • Avoid on server machines or with sensitive services.
; NOTE: Speed/Comfort setting: makes shutdowns faster, recommended for well maintained personal PCs, use with caution if complex services are running in the background.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control]
"WaitToKillServiceTimeout"="3000"

; KORSiOS - [System]• Shutdown • Time to Kill Apps Timeout > 3000
; ID: System_TimeToKillAppsTimeout
; DESC: Reduces the wait time before forcibly closing unresponsive applications.
; IMPACT: • Windows considers an application frozen after 2 seconds of inactivity.
; IMPACT: • Windows waits 3 seconds before forcibly closing an application during logoff, shutdown, or restart.
; IMPACT: • Makes logoffs and shutdowns faster.
; RISK: • Loss of unsaved data if an application is closed too quickly.
; RISK: • Some resource intensive applications (video editing, rendering, VMs, IDEs) may require more time to close properly.
; RISK: • Not recommended for users who frequently leave critical tasks running.
; NOTE: Responsiveness/Speed ​​setting: speeds up Windows shutdown and reduces freezes caused by unresponsive apps, ideal for daily use provided you save your work regularly.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\Desktop]
"WaitToKillAppTimeout"="3000"
"HungAppTimeout"="2000"

; KORSiOS - [System]• Maintenance • Prevent certain reinstallations / Microsoft suggestions
; ID: System_ConsumerFeatures
; DESC: Disables consumer features and suggested Windows apps.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from installing or promoting consumer apps (games, App Store, Microsoft services).
; IMPACT: • Reduces suggestions, promotional content, and automatic installations after updates.
; IMPACT: • Contributes to a cleaner, more business oriented Windows experience.
; RISK: • Fewer app discoveries for consumer users.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Debloat/system cleanup setting: Prevents automatic addition of "consumer" content.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\CloudContent]
"DisableWindowsConsumerFeatures"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [System]• Compatibility • Enable Long File Paths
; ID: System_EnableLongFilesPaths
; DESC: Enables support for long file paths (beyond 260 characters).
; IMPACT: • Removes the historical 260 character limit (MAX_PATH) for compatible applications.
; IMPACT: • Facilitates working with deep directory trees (development, scripts, archives, complex projects).
; RISK: • Compatibility: Some older, incompatible applications may still fail with long paths.
; RISK: • No impact on system stability or security.
; NOTE: Compatibility/productivity setting: essential for development and technical environments; removes an archaic Windows limitation.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\FileSystem]
"LongPathsEnabled"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [System]• Security • Disables Windows SmartScreen
; ID: System_DisableSmartScreen
; DESC: Disables Windows SmartScreen at the system level.
; IMPACT: • Prevents SmartScreen from checking the reputation of downloaded applications and files.
; IMPACT: • Suppresses "unrecognized application" alerts and blocks based on cloud reputation.
; IMPACT: • Facilitates the execution of custom tools, scripts, and unsigned software.
; RISK: • Increased security risk: less protection against malware or unknown software.
; RISK: • Dangerous downloads and executions may proceed without warning.
; RISK: • Strongly discouraged without user vigilance or an alternative security solution.
; NOTE: Freedom/Advanced Control setting: useful for expert users and controlled environments, but use with caution on exposed systems.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\System]
"EnableSmartScreen"=dword:00000000
"ShellSmartScreenLevel"="Off"
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer]
"SmartScreenEnabled"="Off"
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\AppHost]
"EnableWebContentEvaluation"=dword:00000000
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Edge]
"SmartScreenEnabled"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [System]• Maintenance • Disable Windows Auto-Maintenance
; ID: System_DisableAutoMaintenance
; DESC: Disables Windows automatic maintenance.
; IMPACT: • Prevents scheduled maintenance tasks from running (optimization, diagnostics, updates for certain apps, background scans).
; IMPACT: • Reduces automatic CPU/disk activity when the PC is idle.
; IMPACT: • Prevents system tasks from starting without user action.
; RISK: • No automatic maintenance (disk optimization, checks, certain updates).
; RISK: • May lead to gradual degradation if maintenance is not performed manually.
; RISK: • No immediate risk to stability.
; NOTE: Full control : useful for preventing unwanted automatic activity. For users who perform regular manual maintenance only.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Schedule\Maintenance]
"MaintenanceDisabled"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [System]• Diagnostics • Disable automatic reboot for BSODs
; ID: System_DisableAutoReboot
; DESC: Prevents automatic restart after a crash (BSOD).
; IMPACT: • Forces Windows to remain stuck on the blue screen after a crash.
; IMPACT: • Allows reading the error code and diagnosing the problem.
; IMPACT: • Useful for debugging, overclocking, and unstable drivers.
; RISK: • The PC no longer restarts automatically after a crash.
; RISK: • Requires manual intervention.
; RISK: • No risk to stability.
; NOTE: Debug/diagnostic setting: essential for analyzing BSODs.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\CrashControl]
"AutoReboot"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Tips / Tricks] Disable Windows Tips & Tricks
; ID: Tips_DisableTips
; DESC: Disables "Soft Landing," i.e., promotional suggestions and content after updates or upon first use.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from displaying recommendations, sponsored tips, and suggested apps.
; IMPACT: • Reduces notifications and "discovery" screens after a Windows upgrade or a new session.
; IMPACT: • Contributes to a cleaner and less intrusive experience.
; RISK: • Loss of discovery information for new users.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or performance.
; NOTE: Anti-promotional content setting / Clean UX: Prevents Windows from "pushing" apps or services after updates, perfect for a clean and controlled setup.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\CloudContent]
"DisableSoftLanding"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Windows Defender]• Notifications • Disables Windows Defender notifications
; ID: Defender_DisableNotifications
; DESC: Disables notifications from the Windows Defender Security Center.
; IMPACT: • Suppresses security related alerts and notifications (antivirus, firewall, account protection).
; IMPACT: • The Security Center continues to function and protect the system, but without visible notifications.
; RISK: • Missed critical security alerts (threats detected, protection disabled).
; RISK: • May delay the user's response to a security issue.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or performance.
; NOTE: Silence/Control setting: Reduces the noise of security notifications; use only on an actively monitored or controlled system.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows Defender Security Center\Notifications]
"DisableNotifications"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Windows Defender]• Cloud • Disables participation in Microsoft Defender Cloud
; ID: Defender_DisableDefenderCloud
; DESC: Disables participation in Microsoft Defender Cloud (SpyNet) and automatic sample submission.
; IMPACT: • Disables membership in Microsoft Defender Cloud Protection (SpyNet).
; IMPACT: • Prevents the automatic submission of suspicious files to Microsoft.
; IMPACT: • Defender's local protection remains active, but without cloud scanning or sample submission.
; RISK: • Potentially slower detection of very recent (zero-day) threats without the cloud.
; RISK: • Fewer real-time alerts based on online reputation.
; RISK: • No impact on stability or performance.
; NOTE: Privacy setting / security control: limits data exchange with Microsoft while keeping the local antivirus.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows Defender\Spynet]
"SpyNetReporting"=dword:00000000
"SubmitSamplesConsent"=dword:00000002

; KORSiOS - [Windows Defender]• Real-time • Reduce real-time protection
; ID: Defender_ReduceProtection
; DESC: Disables several components of Microsoft Defender's real•time protection.
; IMPACT: • Disables behavioral monitoring (detection based on process activity).
; IMPACT: • Disables file scanning on open/execution.
; IMPACT: • Prevents automatic scanning when real-time protection is enabled.
; IMPACT: • Significantly reduces Defender's background activity (CPU, disk, I/O latency).
; RISK: • High security risk: threats can execute without being blocked in real time.
; RISK: • Primarily reactive protection instead of preventative.
; RISK: • Strongly discouraged without an alternative security solution or a highly controlled environment.
; NOTE: Advanced antivirus disabling setting: reserved for expert users (lab, VM, extreme gaming, offline systems). Use only if safety is ensured by other means.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows Defender\Real-Time Protection]
"DisableBehaviorMonitoring"=dword:00000001
"DisableOnAccessProtection"=dword:00000001
"DisableScanOnRealtimeEnable"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Windows Defender]• Scan • Disable scheduled scans
; ID: Defender_DisableScheduledScans
; DESC: Disables scheduled scans by Microsoft Defender.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Defender from running scheduled automatic scans.
; IMPACT: • Reduces background CPU/disk activity at potentially inconvenient times.
; IMPACT: • Manual scans are still possible if Defender is still active.
; RISK: • Less proactive threat detection without regular scans.
; RISK: • Persistent infections may remain undetected for longer.
; RISK: • To be avoided without regular manual scans or an alternative security solution.
; NOTE: Performance setting / antivirus control: useful for avoiding resource intensive automatic scans, but should be combined with a clear security strategy.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows Defender\Scan]
"DisableScheduledScans"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Windows Defender]• Detection • Disable protection against potentially unwanted applications
; ID: Defender_DisableUnwantedApps
; DESC: Disables Microsoft Defender's protection against potentially unwanted applications (PUAs).
; IMPACT: • Prevents Defender from blocking or reporting PUAs (adware, toolbars, intrusive software).
; IMPACT: • Reduces alerts and blocks when installing certain unsigned or borderline software.
; IMPACT: • May facilitate the installation of custom or outdated tools.
; RISK: • Increased risk of installing unwanted or adware software.
; RISK: • Less protection against bundlers and dubious installers.
; RISK: • No direct impact on system stability.
; NOTE: Installation freedom/control setting: useful for advanced users who know what they are installing, but should be avoided on exposed systems or by inexperienced users.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows Defender]
"PUAProtection"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Windows Defender]• Scan • Disable CPU throttling
; ID: Defender_DisableCPUThrottling
; DESC: Disables the CPU throttling applied by Microsoft Defender during background scans.
; IMPACT: • Prevents Defender from reducing CPU usage during so-called "idle" scans.
; IMPACT: • Scans run faster, even in the background.
; IMPACT: • May reduce the total scan time, at the cost of a more noticeable CPU load.
; RISK: • Higher CPU spikes during automatic or manual scans.
; RISK: • May temporarily impact responsiveness if a scan starts during heavy activity.
; RISK: • No direct security or stability risk.
; NOTE: Performance setting / fast scans: speeds up Defender scans at the expense of discretion.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows Defender\Performance]
"DisableCpuThrottleOnIdleScans"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Windows Update]• Notifications • Disable notifications
; ID: Update_DisableNotifications
; DESC: Disables the indication of availability for a major Windows upgrade.
; IMPACT: • Forces Windows to consider that no upgrade is available.
; IMPACT: • Prevents the display of notifications and prompts offering a Windows upgrade.
; IMPACT: • Reduces prompts related to version changes.
; RISK: • Intentionally delays new versions: the user can remain on a given version longer.
; RISK: • Major upgrades will need to be initiated manually if desired.
; RISK: • No impact on regular security updates.
; NOTE: Anti-push upgrade setting: useful for keeping a stable system locked onto a known version, while continuing to receive security patches.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\Setup\UpgradeNotification]
"UpgradeAvailable"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Windows Update]• Privacy • Disable diagnostic data (MRT)
; ID: Update_DisableMRT
; DESC: Prevents the Malware Removal Tool (MRT) from sending information to Microsoft.
; IMPACT: • Disables the sending of infection reports detected by MRT during its monthly run.
; IMPACT: • MRT malware scanning and removal continue to function normally.
; IMPACT: • Reduces security related telemetry sent to Microsoft.
; RISK: • Less data reported to Microsoft, which may reduce the overall improvement of the tool.
; RISK: • No impact on local protection or system stability.
; NOTE: Privacy setting: maintains MRT protection while blocking external reporting, consistent with a more discreet Windows approach.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\MRT]
"DontReportInfectionInformation"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Windows Update]• Stability • Disable the Windows Insider Program
; ID: Update_DisableInsiderProgram
; DESC: Disables participation in Windows preview builds (Insider/Preview Builds).
; IMPACT: • Prevents Windows from offering or installing test builds and Insider builds.
; IMPACT: • The system remains only on stable and officially released versions.
; IMPACT: • Prevents notifications prompting you to join preview programs.
; RISK: • Loss of early access to new Windows features.
; RISK: • No impact on stability, security, or regular security updates.
; NOTE: Stability/Production setting: ensures a stable Windows, without experimental builds, ideal for a controlled and reliable configuration.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\PreviewBuilds]
"AllowBuildPreview"=dword:00000000

; KORSiOS - [Windows Update]• Notifications • Disable Windows upgrade/restart notifications
; ID: Update_DisableRestartNotification
; DESC: Hides the link to the Media Creation Tool and disables restart notifications related to Windows Update.
; IMPACT: • Hides the link to the Media Creation Tool in the Windows Update interface.
; IMPACT: • Disables notifications prompting a restart after updates.
; IMPACT: • A more discreet Windows Update experience, with fewer pop-ups and prompts.
; RISK: • Less visibility into the need to restart.
; RISK: • Manual access to the Media Creation Tool is still possible.
; NOTE: Comfort/Anti-notification setting: Reduces the noise of Windows Update and prevents unwanted restarts.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\WindowsUpdate\UX\Settings]
"HideMCTLink"=dword:00000001
"RestartNotificationsAllowed2"=dword:00000000

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\WindowsUpdate]
"SetAutoRestartNotificationDisable"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Windows Update]• Restart • Disable automatic restart when the user is logged in
; ID: Update_DisableRestartUserLog
; DESC: Prevents Windows from automatically restarting after an update when a user is logged in.
; IMPACT: • Blocks forced Windows Update restarts as long as a user session is active.
; IMPACT: • Updates are still installed, but a restart must be initiated manually.
; IMPACT: • Prevents sudden interruptions during work, gaming, or rendering.
; RISK: • Delayed restart: Some critical updates are only fully active after a reboot.
; RISK: • If the user forgets to restart, the system may temporarily remain in a "waiting" state.
; NOTE: Comfort/Anti-interruption setting: Protects the user session from unexpected restarts.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\WindowsUpdate\AU]
"NoAutoRebootWithLoggedOnUsers"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Windows Update]• Update • Disable automatic updates
; ID: Update_DisableUpdate
; DESC: Prevents Windows Update from automatically downloading and installing updates.
; IMPACT: • Disables automatic installation of updates via Windows Update.
; IMPACT: • Windows will no longer automatically download updates in the background.
; IMPACT: • Updates will have to be launched manually from Settings.
; RISK: • Risk of delay in security patches.
; RISK: • Vulnerabilities not fixed if user forgets to update manually.
; RISK: • Some versions of Windows 11 partially ignore this key (Microsoft bypasses certain policies).
; RISK: • Windows may reactivate certain behaviors after a major update (feature update).
; NOTE: Not recommended on a permanently connected PC without regular maintenance.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\WindowsUpdate\AU]
"NoAutoUpdate"=dword:00000001

; KORSiOS - [Windows Update]• Update • Configure Windows Update in “Notify before download”
; ID: Update_NotifUpdate
; DESC: Configures Windows Update to notify the user before downloading updates.
; IMPACT: • Windows displays a notification before downloading updates.
; IMPACT: • Updates are no longer downloaded automatically.
; IMPACT: • Reduces unwanted background downloads.
; RISK: • Risk of delayed updates if the user ignores notifications.
; RISK: • On certain Home editions, Windows may partially ignore the policy.
; RISK: • Some versions of Windows 11 partially ignore this key (Microsoft bypasses certain policies).
; RISK: • Windows may reactivate certain behaviors after a major update (feature update).
; NOTE: Balanced “Update Control” setting: Recommended for maintaining control without completely disabling Windows Update.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Policies\Microsoft\Windows\WindowsUpdate\AU]
"AUOptions"=dword:00000002

; KORSiOS - [Windows Update]• Stockage • Disable storage reserved for Windows Update
; ID: Update_DisableReservedStockage
; DESC: Disables the “Reserved Storage” mechanism used by Windows to reserve disk space for updates.
; IMPACT: • Prevent Windows from maintaining a reserved disk space for future updates.
; IMPACT: • Can free up several GB of disk space (depending on configuration).
; IMPACT: • Reduce the “invisible” disk consumption associated with Windows Update.
; RISK: • May cause Windows Update errors if disk space becomes insufficient.
; RISK: • Windows can recreate the reserved storage after certain feature updates.
; NOTE: A useful setting on small capacity SSDs (128/256 GB) to recover space.
; RESTART: REBOOT
[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\ReserveManager]
"ShippedWithReserves"=dword:00000000